title: mock cheese cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: puttanesca pasta sauce
directions: Cut olives into small pieces.
In large skillet, heat oil over low heat.
Add garlic and cook, stirring 1 minute or until golden. Stir in tomatoes with juice, roasted pepper, tomato paste, olives, capers, oregano and red pepper.
Cook over medium heat about 15 minutes until sauce thickens.
Stir in anchovies and parsley and simmer 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and cool. Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fat-pinto beans
directions: Clean pinto beans.
Rinse and let soak in water all night. The next day, boil pinto beans
with salt and onion.
The beans will be big, fat pinto beans.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Cook rice. Combine sauteed vegetables, soups, rice, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and salt.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° until it bubbles around edges and in the middle, approximately 30 minutes.

title: banana nut oatmeal bread
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add to the sugar mixture eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt alternately with bananas with the sugar mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Pour into 3 medium or 2 large lightly greased glass loaf pans.
Bake 5 minutes in microwave on High or Roast/Medium to keep the tops from cracking.
Can be baked in a regular oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend cake mix, 1 egg and margarine together.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Blend together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, combine softened cream cheese with both types of olives, onions, and Tabasco sauce; mix thoroughly. Set cheese mixture in refrigerator about 15 minutes to harden slightly for easier handling. Shape cheese mixture into ball. Roll in chopped parsley to coat well. Return to refrigerator, chill 15 to 20 minutes or until serving. Serve with assorted crackers. If made day ahead, wrap loosely in wax paper. Leftovers can be used as a sandwich spread on rye bread for lunch.

title: yellow layer cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add and mix remaining ingredients. Bake 40 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and frost.

title: baked eggs
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Mix together and pour over 6 slices bread pieces in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover and set overnight in refrigerator.
Put in oven and bake 45 or 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and chopped onion in water until tender.
Drain. Add soup, salt, pepper and mix well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Pour in 1/2 of dried onions and stir.
Cover with remaining onions and shredded cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix both soups and Ro-Tel until well blended.
Coarsely crush chips
by
pounding
on a slightly open bag.
Spray the bottom
of a
x
9-inch casserole dish with Pam and richly cover
with chips.
Add a generous layer of chicken and cover with
1/2 of the soup mixture.
Repeat all layers and top with cheese.
Bake
in
a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with a salad.
No need for bread.
This is wonderful!

title: creamy pineapple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrot in large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients.
Add to cabbage mixture, tossing gently. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter. Remove from heat to cool. Add sugar. Mix well. When cool, add flour and beaten eggs. Mix well. Add salt and vanilla. Mix. Put in 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool before cutting. Enjoy!

title: cream cheese bars
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan spread 1 can crescent roll mix.
In separate bowl beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk until creamy.
Spread on the crescent roll mix, then spread second crescent roll on top, pinch all sections together.
Brush egg white on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cooking too long dries the squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas in a bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking soda together.
Add to bananas.
If using nuts, add now.
Stir well.
Put in a buttered loaf pan and bake at 350°.

title: hayley's spiced pecans(yields 2 cups)
directions: Melt butter and add spices.
Coat the nuts in this mixture and toast them at 375° until brown (20 to 30 minutes).
Shake the nuts occasionally as they toast.
Drain on brown paper.

title: louisiana macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain off fat.
In ungreased 2-quart casserole, mix macaroni, beef and remaining ingredients, except potato chips.
Cover; bake for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle top with chips.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: pasta seafood salad
directions: Cool elbow macaroni as directed on package; drain, rinse with cold water and hold aside.
Blanch broccoli in boiling water for 5 minutes, drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine elbow macaroni, broccoli, green and red peppers, olives and tuna fish.
Add Italian dressing and toss gently, but well.
Makes 13 1/2 cups or 8 servings.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper and set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix and set aside.
To assemble/layer: Spread bean dip on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with avocado mixture.
Spread sour cream mixture on top of this.
Sprinkle with onions, jalapeno peppers and/or olives, then tomatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: french cream cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Make crumbs of vanilla wafers.
Place 1/2 in bottom of buttered pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Whip cream; add pineapple and nuts.
Pour over 1st mixture.
Cover with remainder of crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat berries, sugar and jello just to melt.
Mix pudding and milk. Add sour cream.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, pudding and strawberries. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberry and mint leaf.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Then beat in vanilla and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Sift flour and baking soda and beat mixture into butter mixture in 3 parts, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in rhubarb. Pour batter in standard 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Blend sugar and remaining cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Bake until toothpick comes clean, 45 minutes at 375°.
Top with whipped cream.

title: spooky pudding
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed on the package.
Pour pudding into 4 dessert dishes.
Set pudding in refrigerator to chill for 5 minutes.

title: cream chicken on egg bread
directions: Brown onion and celery in butter.
Add flour to chicken broth.
Add peas, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Add cooked chicken and cook until thick.
Make your favorite corn bread and cut in squares.
Cover with cream chicken.

title: henry's pork chops
directions: In skillet with margarine, add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Cook until brown.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup, hamburger, egg, onion, bread crumbs, milk, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Put in a 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with 2 cups mashed potatoes and top with remaining soup.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top. Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: white bark cookies
directions: Melt together white bark and peanut butter.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with bark mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: bakery cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine the mashed potatoes and potato water. Add the shortening, blend well.
Add the salt, sugar and egg.
In a small bowl, combine yeast and lukewarm water, stir until dissolved; add to the potato mixture.
Add the milk alternately with the flour.
Knead dough, place in a large bowl.
Grease the top of the dough with oleo.
Place in the refrigerator overnight. Grease two 9 x 13-inch baking pans, turn the dough onto a floured board.
Roll out a large, even pastry.
In a bowl, mix a generous amount of brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon.
Sprinkle the mixture over the rolled out dough.
Make several large rolls from the pastry and then cut individual buns from the rolls.
Place on the prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Watch the rolls carefully.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with crescent rolls. Pinch seams together. Brown sausage and drain. Add cream cheese and stir until smooth. Spread sausage mixture over crescent rolls. Top with 2nd can crescent rolls. Cook according to crescent roll directions.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: You will also need a 9 x 13 glass baking dish.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oats and boiling water; cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to oats mixture; mix thoroughly with a spoon until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oat 'n raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In a large bowl beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion.
Brown beef.
Wash and drain.
Add beans and 1/2 cup water.
Add chili powder, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes or until gravy thickens, stirring frequently.

title: kartoffelsalat(german potato salad)
directions: In a skillet, combine all ingredients except potatoes, sour cream and parsley.
Add potatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Simmer 25 minutes or until done.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: kitty's kasserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season to taste.
Drain excess fat. Boil noodles while meat is frying.
Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wilted red cabbage and bell pepper slaw
directions: In a saucepan, bring vinegar and water to a boil with sugar, salt and mustard seed; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes.

title: allspice wassail bowl punch
directions: Combine.
(Tie cloves and allspice in cheesecloth.) Cover. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with a cinnamon stick in each mug.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together the flour, soda, powder and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat the margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Beat in sugars until well blended, then add eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls. Flatten with fork dipped in water. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes a lot of cookies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Put meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Drain beans and put beans on top of meat.
Place Tater Tots evenly on top of casserole.
Put soup in separate pan to mix well.
Pour soup over casserole and then place in hot oven.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: enchilada suisa
directions: Remove papery husks from tomatillos.
Wash tomatillos and chiles well.
Cook, covered, in a little boiling water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove stems and seeds from chiles. Place chiles and drained tomatillos in blender container.
Add onion, garlic and cilantro and blend until pureed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl; add walnuts. Add eggs, pumpkin, oil and water.
Blend lightly.
Pour into 2 greased bread tins and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: macaroni and cheese and spam casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed, except use 3/4 cup milk.
Add peas and soup; mix well.
Pour into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Arrange meat squares in checkerboard pattern.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: In a large bowl, cream the shortening, brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well. Stir in oatmeal, apples, nuts and raisins.
Spread in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut in squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: tropical cream pie
directions: Put pineapple juice, cream cheese, sugar, coconut and extract in blender.
Cover and process until well mixed.
Remove to bowl and add pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched with finger.
Cool in pan.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Roll in flour.
Brown in cooking oil; place in casserole dish.
Make a little brown gravy in oil where you browned chicken and add mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken and bake at 325° until done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry instant pudding mix with pineapple.
Fold in pecans, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: polish sausage appetizer
directions: Put sausage pieces in baking dish.
Pour undrained pineapple and chili sauce over sausage.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fish stuffed bell pepper(appetizer)
directions: Grind fish or put through food processor.
Saute onions and parsley in olive oil.
Add 1 cup wine, chopped garlic, Louisiana hot sauce, soy sauce, salt and chopped pepper.
Cook until onions and pepper are done or real tender.
Let cool for a few minutes.

title: pork chops with amber rice
directions: Brown
chops
in skillet.
Salt and pepper.
Place rice in Pyrex
baking
dish; pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange browned pork
chops
over	rice.
Pour chicken rice soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: dream salad
directions: Boil water with lemon and lime jello for 3 minutes.
Then add pineapple and boil 3 minutes more.
Chill until partially set. Stir in tub of cottage cheese and marshmallows. Then whip cream cheese (or use Cool Whip) and fold into other ingredients and let set.
Add nuts.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Heat oil on medium; saute onion and garlic for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a slow simmer for at least 2 hours.
Let cool slightly before serving for maximum flavor.
Serve with toasted Cuban or French bread for dipping.

title: vanilla taffy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil, over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, without stirring, to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and margarine.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Pull candy with fingers until it has a satin-like finish and milky-white color.
Pull into long strips 3/4-inch wide.
Cut into 1-inch pieces with scissors.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix coconut and pecans.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. When cut, turn squares upside down.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in pie pan.
Mix and pat around pan. Ready to bake.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as per directions on box. While it is still hot, punch full of holes. Boil milk, sugar and coconut for 10 minutes. Pour over cake. Cool completely. Top with 8-ounce container of Cool Whip. Put rest of coconut on top. Keep in refrigerator.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Cook ground beef and bacon; drain. Combine all ingredients, except bacon in casserole dish. Lay bacon strips on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: liver and onions
directions: In hot oil, cook onions 10 to 15 minutes, until very tender, stirring often.
Remove onions to platter; keep warm.
Cut liver into 4 portions.
Coat liver with flour.
In same skillet, over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons oil, cook liver 4 minutes or until browned on both sides, turning once.
Place liver on onions. Serve hot.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut the
steak	into
slices
1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and
pepper.
In
a
large skillet heat the oil, add the steak, onion and garlic; cook until the meat is browned on all sides.
Add
the
green
peppers
and
bouillon, cover and simmer 10	minutes.
Add
the
tomatoes
and simmer 5 minutes. Mix the cornstarch	or
flour,
soy sauce, and water and stir into the meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until the mixture has thickened. Serve with hot boiled rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, chili, chicken broth, together.
Cut tortillas, bite size.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cut olives bite size as well.
In a 2 quart casserole dish, layer starting with the soup mixture, chicken, olives, tortillas and cheese.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Put in oven at 350 degrees until it bubbles, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken-stuffing delight
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
In bottom of baking dish put the chicken.
Add soup.
Cover with Stove Top and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour; add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves the side of bowl.
Turn out onto floured board; knead just until smooth.

title: baked chicken with orange nut rice
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels. Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Coat chicken pieces on all sides with flour mixture. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and brown on all sides.

title: finger paint
directions: Combine flour and water, mix until creamy. Add detergent, mix well. Add food coloring, mixing well. Store in air tight container. Have fun!

title: jessie's divinity
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and cook for 19 minutes on High in microwave in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, apple, celery and dill.
Stir curry powder into mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Add more curry powder, if desired.
Fold in cream.
Spoon curry mayonnaise over chicken mixture; toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with egg slices and tomato wedges.

title: romanoff fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and celery in a bowl.
Stir remaining ingredients together and stir into salad mixture.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: curry chicken
directions: Mix chicken, salt, pepper, curry, onion and green pepper together.
Cover bottom of heavy Dutch oven with desired type cooking oil.
Slightly brown chicken mixture, then add vegetables and liquids.
Cover; simmer until chicken is very tender (30 to 40 minutes).

title: beef casserole for a crowd
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add cooked noodles, soups and Cheez Whiz.
Prepare and drain mixed vegetables.
Add to beef mixture.

title: chili
directions: Saute sausage and beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in a large heavy saucepan until browned, stirring to crumble sausage. Drain excess grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Additional water may be added if needed. Yields 8 servings.

title: oven-fried yellow squash
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine egg and water; beat well.
Dip squash in egg mixture.
Lightly coat a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with vegetable spray.
Place squash slices in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.

title: five pound fudge
directions: Bring milk, sugar and butter to a boil stirring continually. Boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat, add chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir until melted, add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan to cool.
Cut into squares, turn out onto wax paper and separate.

title: black bean soup
directions: Clean and wash the black beans.
Cover beans and soak overnight.
Use same water, medium onion (chopped finely) and salt to taste.
Add garlic, if desired.
Allow beans to boil until the liquid has thickened and has nearly boiled away.
Put the beans through a food grinder.
This will be a paste.
Chop the small onion and fry in the shortening.
Add paste with sufficient water to make desired thickness.
Cook slowly for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with croutons or fried tortilla strips.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Melt butter and pour over bread.
Cut into cubes.
Place mustard, egg yolks, milk and grated cheese together. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in egg mixture. Pour in buttered baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy bean soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil.
Simmer about 1 hour, covered and 30 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Blend butter, sugar and dates; bring to a boil.
Let cool. Add other ingredients and roll into small balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and bell
pepper
in butter.
Boil chicken. Debone.
Set broth aside.
To
sauteed
onion
add soups, sour cream, milk, salsa and half
of both cheeses.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Some may
prefer more garlic powder.
Grease baking dish. Boil chicken broth,
dipping
each	flour
tortilla
in broth to soften.
Put
tablespoon mixture in tortilla, roll and fold ends.
When baking dish if full put remaining mixture over tortillas.	Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: peanut candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook until syrup begins to brown.
Remove from fire.
Add peanuts, baking soda and flavoring.
Pour quickly into well buttered, shallow pan.
When cold, cut in squares.

title: sour cream substitute
directions: Combine water and cheese in blender on high speed for 20 seconds or until cheese is liquified.
Mix remaining ingredients. Serve on salads, baked potatoes or as a dip.

title: chicken salsa casserole
directions: Bake chicken in foil for 1 hour at 400°, then bone.
Cut in large pieces.
Season.
Cut tortillas in strips.
Mix soup, milk, onion and chili salsa.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all the ingredients, except the ketchup.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook it over moderately low heat for 20 minutes.
The sauce should be thick.
Stir in ketchup and remove sauce from heat.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix well until blended.
If sticky, add powdered sugar until desired consistency.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream the cheese, margarine and flour together.
Press into miniature muffin tins, sides also (makes 24).
Blend vanilla, margarine, egg, brown sugar and pecans.
Fill tarts 3/4 full. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Place pecans on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: vegetable tofu salad
directions: Marinate tofu for 1 hour in mixture of oil, tamari, vinegar, water, honey and garlic.
Combine tofu with celery, mushrooms and cabbage.
Serve.

title: souper chicken
directions: Place all together in a baking pan.
Place chicken on top and season.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup (dry) on top.
Cook, covered, until chicken is done.
Full time 1 1/2 hours; 400°, 1/2 hour; 350°, 1 hour.

title: liverwurst pate
directions: Mix sausage, onion, mayonnaise and horseradish; form into a ball.
Cover with softened cream cheese (soften with a bit of milk and Tabasco sauce, to taste).
Roll in dry parsley.

title: walnut raspberry brownie
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening over warm water; cool slightly. Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add flour and stir.
Add nuts; stir.
Pour into well-greased square pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Spread jam over hot brownies.

title: party salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon thoroughly. Flake carefully. Combine with softened cream cheese. Add next 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly. Cover bowl. Refrigerate a few hours, until firm. Shape salmon into ball; roll in pecans. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap; return to the refrigerator until serving. If using fish mold, use 2 cans of salmon.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: (Add 1/2 teaspoon or more of each spice if you like your tea highly spiced.)

title: luscious lemon
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix next three ingredients and spread on crust after crust is cool.
Mix pudding with milk and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: rice chex treats
directions: Melt all ingredients, except cereal and sugar, together.
Pour over cereal, then put in bag of confectioners sugar and shake to coat.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water, syrup and salt. Cook until clear.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and food coloring; stir to dissolve.
Cool completely.
Mix berries in gently; pour into pie shell.
Chill served with Cool Whip.

title: red wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze.
Just before serving, maybe 1 hour, add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: easy apple moon pies
directions: Separate biscuits and, one at a time, on floured board, roll out flat.
Place about 1/2 cup apples on biscuit.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Dot with butter and a dash of cinnamon.
Fold dough over and crimp edges.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until nice and brown.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Mix
salt, alum,
pickling
spice
and	cucumbers
with enough vinegar
to cover.
Let set 3 months; drain and rinse. Drain thoroughly again.
Cut cucumbers in thick slices and put back in gallon jar and cover with 8 cups sugar.

title: herby hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into patties.
Brown on both sides in large skillet.
Pour soup and milk that has been mixed together over patties.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
The gravy is wonderful over mashed potatoes.

title: refrigerated fruit cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and condensed milk.
Add cherries, pineapple, and nuts.
Pour into lined loaf pan.
Cover with wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs until light and add. Add lemon juice to mashed bananas.
Blend with creamed mixture. Sift dry ingredients together and mix into creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° about 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in small amount of water.
Drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Fold in vegetables.
Prepare stuffing mix. Spread half in a 12 x 7-inch dish.
Spoon in vegetables.
Top with remaining mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: best ever homemade pizza
directions: Let rise 2 hours.
Spread onto pizza pan and pie.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler and cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Can be served either hot or cold with baked ham.
This has been a holiday "must" in our family since the early 1950's.
It will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: You will need a 1 pound can or plastic container with lid and a 3 pound can or plastic container with lid.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar. Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Soak raisins in orange juice for 5 minutes.
Do not drain.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs; stir in pumpkin, sugar, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Add oil, mixing well.
Stir together flours, baking powder and soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture with the raisin-orange juice mixture and stir to mix.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Yields 18.
Serving size:

title: chocolate funny pie(no crust)
directions: Blend the butter, sugar and cocoa, then blend flour and salt. Blend in eggs one at a time and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: canoli shells
directions: Cream Ricotta cheese.
Whip the whipping cream.
Add confectioners sugar to cream.
Mix cheese and cream; mix well. Cut up very fine the cherries, chocolate and watermelon rind. Then mix all together with cheese and cream.

title: jean's original pumpkin bread
directions: Beat the eggs well and add sugar; mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients with a hand mixer for 2 minutes. Place batter in bread pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350°.
To bake 3 large loaves, bake 1 hour.
To bake 6 small loaves, bake 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Into a rectangular pan (9 x 13-inch), dump crushed pineapple (juice and all).
Dump cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over this.
Sprinkle box of cake mix over the mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over this.
Chip margarine over all this.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook beef and onion together.
Add mushrooms, soup and salt. Heat until bubbly.
Add sour cream just before serving.
This is good served over rice or wide noodles.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with garlic, salt and pepper; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: sunrise punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a pitcher, stir well and chill. Fill each of 6 tall thin glasses with ice, and add orange juice mixture.
Slowly pour 1/2 teaspoon grenadine down inside of each glass (do not stir before serving).
Garnish with lime slices, if desired.

title: ham and turkey loaf
directions: Chop ham (I use processor); mix with turkey.
Add onion and eggs; mix well.
Break bread into pieces; pour milk over it.
Stir to break up bread, then add to meat.
Combine well.
Spray loaf pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom; sprinkle pineapple juice over sugar.
Place 3 pineapple rings over sugar.
Carefully spoon meat mixture over pineapple.
Place loaf pan in larger pan with 1 inch water in larger pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place 3 more pineapple rings on top; bake 15 minutes longer.
Add more water, if needed.
To serve, loosen edges and invert loaf onto platter. Serve leftovers cold later.

title: garlic mashed red potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and garlic in a large saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the potatoes are very tender. Drain well. Add the butter, milk and salt; mash. Stir in Parmesan cheese.

title: frosted marshmallow brownies
directions: Mix
sugar and cocoa, then add shortening.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add vanilla, flour, salt and nuts.
Bake in a jelly roll pan, 17 x 11-inch, at 350° for 18 minutes.
Remove from oven
and cover with a 10 1/2 ounce package of miniature marshmallows. Bake
for
more	minutes
longer.
Cool	and frost.

title: chocolate dipped pretzels
directions: Dip pretzels in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Let set until chocolate hardens.
To store, place in airtight container.

title: no cholesterol white pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Whip egg whites into soft peaks.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Add lemon flavoring.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oleo and milk.
Add to corn, then add sugar, salt, pepper and eggs.
Crumble saltine cracker crumbs and add to corn mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chopped liver dip(pate)
directions: Saute chicken
livers and onions in the salad oil.
Add salt to	taste.	Put
in
blender
to
mush with 4 hard-boiled eggs. To moisten use a little oil you cooked with.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, Crisco and salt and mix with hands or cut in with a knife.
Add cream or water and mix until you have a dough mixture you can make into a ball.
Take small balls, about what you would need for a single pie crust, and wrap in Ziploc bags and store in the freezer until you are ready to use them.
You will have about 17 individual pie crusts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food chopper.
Add sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Add marshmallows and apples.
Mix with whipped cream. Garnish with green grapes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a 6 or 9-inch clay pot (flowerpot; I used a plastic one)

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Spread on baked cake and put in oven until topping bubbles.

title: orange glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well mixed. Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are well moistened.
Pour batter into two 9 1/4 x 5 1/2 x 2-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until bread tests done with wooden picks.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove to cooling racks.
Completely cool bread, then drizzle glaze over top and sides.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Bake crusts until light brown.
Break into bite size pieces. Wash and slice strawberries and sweeten to taste.
In a large glass bowl, alternate crust pieces and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: delicious butterhorns
directions: Add butter to milk; scald and stir until butter has melted. Combine yeast and warm water, stir in sugar.
Set aside while combining other ingredients.
Sift flour and salt, add eggs to milk mixture, beat in sifted flour, lemon rind and vanilla.
Add yeast mixture.
When smooth, place in greased bowl and cover with greased wax paper and set in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use, let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Roll 1/2 of dough in a circle, cut into pie shaped wedges and roll up starting in with wide end.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with powdered sugar, nuts and cherries.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and baking powder with salt to taste.
Beat the eggs; add to flour.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix with the buttermilk.
Add oysters and juice.
Heat oil to 375°. Drop with long teaspoon; fry until brown.

title: broccoli nut salad
directions: Break or cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces. Add pecans, raisins, red onions and bacon.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with any kind of crackers as an appetizer or snack.

title: baked banana doughnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray baking sheet with cooking spray. In large bowl, beat bananas, egg whites, oil and brown sugar.
Add flour, oatmeal, baking powder, soda, nuts and spices.
Mix well and let stand for 5 minutes.
Scoop out a heaping tablespoon of dough onto baking sheet.
Using a knife, round out doughnut hole in center of dough, then smooth outside edges of dough into round doughnut shape.
Repeat until all dough is used.
(If dough sticks to knife, spray with cooking spray or dip in water.)
Sprinkle tops with a little sugar and cinnamon, mixed together.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 16 to 18.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/3 cup soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
Brown patties in skillet; drain.
Add remaining soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Blend 1/4 cup water into flour until smooth.
Stir into soup mixture.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
This is a low-fat recipe.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix ingredients and add to 5 cups sliced fresh peaches.
Mix.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in ice cream churn.

title: bacon relish
directions: In a pot, combine brown sugar and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated.
Stir in bacon.
Remove from heat; mix well.
Serve at once.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: holiday drink irish creme
directions: Blend well in blender and let set overnight.

title: frozen barbecued meatballs(makes 80 meatballs)
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into walnut size ball; place meatballs in a single layer on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets. Freeze solid, store in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: chili
directions: Cook over low heat and stir frequently to keep from scorching. Better when made the day before serving.
This will serve 30.

title: chinese chop suey cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels in a double boiler over hot water.
Mix in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and chill.
Serve when chilled thoroughly.
Makes 3/4 dozen.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix and spread on flour tortillas and roll.
Chill overnight and cut in slices.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: pineapple dessert cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball. Roll in pecans or coconut. Serve with cinnamon graham crackers. Very refreshing.

title: granny's broccoli casserole
directions: Steam or boil broccoli (do not over cook).
Put rice, water, broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, onion and salt into baking pan. Mix ingredients lightly.
Dot butter over the top and spread Cheese whiz evenly as possible over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten minestrone
directions: In a slow cooker, combine beef, water, tomatoes, bouillon, onion, parsley, salt, thyme and pepper.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until meat is tender.
Add zucchini, cabbage, beans and macaroni; cook on high, covered, 30 to 45 minutes more or until the vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: no-fat frozen yogurt cake roll
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat the next 3 ingredients with mixer until thickened.
Sprinkle flour mixture over egg mixture.
Using rubber spatula gently fold together. Bake 400°
for 10 to 12 minutes in jelly roll pan lined with wax paper sprayed with cooking spray.
Invert cake on powdered sugar sprinkled towel and roll up quickly.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: pickled polish sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Simmer 1 hour and drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour this mixture over cooled sausage and some chopped onion in a large glass jar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oats and water. Let cool. Combine vegetable oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Mix till smooth. Sift together: flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add to batter. Stir till well blended. Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured 8 x 10 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: walnut casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk and cream.
Add bread crumbs and let stand 20 minutes.
Add onion, walnuts and salt.
Turn into buttered 1-quart baking dish and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fancy deviled ham
directions: Boil eggs.
Mix deviled ham, salt, pepper and salad dressing together.
After eggs are boiled, take 3 of them and chop up and put in mixture.
Take the other 4 and slice up and arrange around the deviled ham mixture.
You could also put lettuce under the eggs you have arranged on the side of the mixture.

title: apple squares
directions: Cream margarine or butter and mix with flour, sugar, egg yolks, sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Spread mixture on greased cookie sheet with sides. Cover with the apples mixed in the sugar and cinnamon topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a pan, boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Mash sweet potatoes, set aside.	In a mixing bowl combine eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk and margarine, mix well; add potatoes and blend until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie crust; bake at 450° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350° bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ground meat and drain.
Mix taco seasoning into ground beef following directions on package.
Using a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, layer tortilla chips on bottom. Sprinkle 1/2 ground beef on top of chips, 1/2 olives, scallions and jalapenos on top of ground beef.
Sprinkle 1/2 of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat for second layer.
Bake in oven 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and nachos are heated through.
Serve hot. Have salsa and sour cream for dipping.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in large pan for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Add bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, Kitchen Bouquet, pepper and salt if needed.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 4 hours.
Pour into crocks; top with toast and Mozzarella cheese.
Put under broiler to melt cheese.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook shells according to directions on box; drain.
Add to meat sauce.
Add 1/4 pound Mozzarella cheese.
Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese.
Add 1 stick pepperoni sliced into quarters.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 pound remaining Mozzarella cheese and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: wedding cake(white)
directions: Mix and bake as directed on box.
Frost with Philly cream cheese frosting.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli, seasoning as desired with salt and pepper. Drain.
(Personally, the mushroom soup has enough seasoning so you don't have to add salt and pepper.
However, you may want to.)

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Stir in 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers.
Put in pie plate.
In frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine and put in 2 cups of sliced Vidalia onions.
Saute until soft.
Pour in pie shell.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour on top of onions.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated sharp cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 3-bean soup in crock-pot
directions: Brown hamburger meat and put in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients and cook all day!
Taste is similar to chili.

title: blueberry crunch 2
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Line pan with crushed pineapple. Add berries.
Pour dry cake mix on that.
Pour butter next and last, nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add Cool Whip until thoroughly mixed.
Add 2 drops each food coloring.
Before removing from mixer, add oranges and pecans.
Pour into pie crusts.
Chill. Can be frozen.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Mix eggs well. Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 19-inch pan.
Bake at 370° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: modified quiche lorraine
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Add cheeses and tuna fish.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix together sugar, egg, milk, and margarine. Stir in flour and baking powder. Pour cherries in greased 9 inch square pan. Spread batter over cherries. Bake at 350 degree for 30 minutes. Makes about six servings.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion together for 5 minutes.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine and mix in flour, salt, pepper and milk. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Blend in cream cheese until smooth. Place broccoli and onion mix in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. (This is my favorite of all broccoli casseroles.)

title: poached trout
directions: In a poaching pan or
a
large	shallow pan, put enough water and white wine (half
and
half) to cover the fish.
Add salt to taste, peppercorns, bay leaf, onion and thyme or dill. Bring the liquid to a boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the fish and enough white wine	to
cover
them,
if
necessary.
Poach gently. Simmer; do not boil, until done.
Cooking should take only approximately 5 minutes.

title: chow chow pickle
directions: Chop all vegetables up.
Put spices in cheesecloth and tie well, so they don't spill in pickle.
Put vegetables, vinegar, water, sugar and spices in kettle.
Cook until well done.
Remove spice bag.
Put in pint jars and process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.

title: orange-ginger glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in the water with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt; drain. Combine sugar, cornstarch, 1/4 teaspoon salt, ginger and orange juice in a saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in butter.
Pour over cooked carrots and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together onion and cream cheese and put in 8-inch pie plate, spreading evenly.
Pour cocktail sauce over this and spread.
Top with mini shrimp.
Chill well before serving with crackers.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 4 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
In large bowl, mix 2 cups sugar and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and juice of orange.
Mix together.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Put 1/2 of batter in greased tube pan (not Bundt pan) and add 1/2 of apple mixture. Cover with remaining batter and top with rest of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients; heat well and serve.

title: marjorie's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, sugar and cocoa. Cream together the shortening, buttermilk and eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix soda and baking powder in water. Add this and vanilla to batter. Bake in 3 layers at 350° until done.

title: orange pineapple sherbet ice cream
directions: Pour drinks into 4-quart ice cream churn.
Mix condensed milk and pineapple into the drinks.
Churn as directed on your ice cream churn.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Spread Cranberries in a well greased 10-inch Pie Plate. Sprinkle with Sugar and Nuts.
In a separate bowl beat eggs: gradually beat in 1 c. Sugar.
Add Flour, Butter and Shortening, beating well.
Pour mixture over Cranberries and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Good served warm or cold with Vanilla Ice Cream.

title: eggplant en casserole
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick after removing skin.
Dice to make 5 cups.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in skillet and saute the eggplant slowly for 5 minutes.
Place in casserole with alternate layers of sliced onions, diced tomatoes and cheese (saving 1/4 cup for to).
Season each layer.
Top with crumb which have been mixed with remaining cheese and dot with remaining butter.
Bake in oven at 375° until vegetables are tender and surface nicely browned, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 5 generous servings.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Top each with marshmallow half, cut side down.
Continue baking until softened. Cool and frost.

title: party fruit salad
directions: Allow cheese to reach room temperature; then beat until creamy and blend in mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients except heavy cream.
Whip cream until stiff and carefully fold into fruit mixture.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Freeze overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer Doritos, 1/2 of chicken, small amount of green pepper and onion, can of cream of chicken soup mixed with 1/3 can milk to make creamier, 1/3 of cheese, then more Doritos, rest of chicken, green pepper and onion, can of cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1/3 can milk to make creamier, 1/2 of remaining cheese, then more Doritos, Ro-Tel tomatoes poured over top and add the last of the cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed. Blend in eggs. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour batter in graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove chicken from bone.
Combine soups and 2 cups chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and chicken.
Pour into a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Fold ingredients together and spoon into 1 pint cartons.
Place in the freezer.

title: bay scallop chowder
directions: Put vegetables in large pot; cover with stock and boil.
Add spices.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Blend with hand blender until pureed or smooth.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add scallops and wine and cook 1 minute. Stir in cream, mixed with egg.
Add to pureed vegetables and broth.
Heat through and serve with sprinkling of parsley.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice to a boil in milk.
Add sugar and salt.
While heating, beat eggs and vanilla together.
Put hot milk mixture in a 2-quart bowl, add eggs and raisins. Set bowl in shallow pan of water.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, stirring after each 15 minutes, the last 15 minutes with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix in top of double boiler the sugar, oleo, water and bourbon.
Put over boiling water.
Mix pecans and crumbs to taste. Using 2 forks, dip cake pieces in bourbon mixture.
Allow excess to drip back into pan.
Roll quickly in crumb mixture in small bowl.
Place on rack to dry.
Store in dry tins.
(Sometimes one runs out of either of the mixes, but remixing takes little time.)

title: breakfast mix with english muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon onto English muffin halves. Broil or bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes until top is golden and cheese is bubbly. Serve with taco chips or crackers.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine muffin mix and butter.
Pat into an ungreased 8-inch square pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes. Beat softened cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir in whipped cream.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with strawberries. Freeze until firm.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef with the onion.
Drain and add chilies, taco sauce and tomato sauce.
Simmer, in saucepan, heat soups and milk over low heat.
Add to meat when heated well.
Cut tortillas in strips and layer with cheese and meat mixture in greased casserole dish. End with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes on 425°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat until thick.
Beat yolks and 1 cup sugar.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Cut up pecans and brown in butter, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar; mix egg mixture together and add pecans.
Stir well or beat mixture thoroughly.
Pour into freezer and fill with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast on water; stir in margarine.
Add 2 cups of flour and salt.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead for 5 minutes until elastic.
Let double.
Cover with your favorite sauce and pizza fixings.

title: pickled okra
directions: Bring vinegar, water, garlic and hot pepper to boil and put salt in each pint on top.
Pack okra in jars.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef along with onions. Add remaining ingredients, including the juices. Cook in crockpot about 1 hour, or until flavors blend. Garnish with taco chips, cheese and sour cream.

title: easy caramel dip for apples
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler or microwave.
Stir in cream cheese until smooth.
Serve with fresh apple slices.

title: ultimate carrot cake
directions: Add all dry ingredients, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add pecans, coconut, carrots and pineapple.
Grease two 9-inch pan (no flour).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: sauerkraut pie
directions: Make up 3 cups mashed potatoes and set aside.
Fry the sausage; drain well.
Wash the sauerkraut and let it drain.
In a large deep dish pie pan, pat 1/2 the mashed potatoes about 1/4-inch thick on the bottom and sides.
Layer 1/2 of the sauerkraut, sausage, cheese and make a second layer using the remaining sauerkraut, sausage and cheese.
Using the rest of the mashed potatoes, pat a crust on top and pinch the ends together.
Rub the dash of butter on the top and sprinkle pepper lightly on the top. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until the top turns a golden brown.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine all ingredients and put on the stove.
Bring to a boil for 5 full minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda while you are stirring all of the ingredients.
Do not add until all has been mixed together.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: In large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta to desired doneness; drain and cool by rinsing in cold water, then drain again.
In large bowl, mix together all remaining ingredients thoroughly but gently; add pasta and toss.
Serve or refrigerate until ready to serve (best served at room temperature).

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion.
Add soup, water, spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and spices to taste.
Simmer.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add mixture and mix well.
Pour half in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with sliced cheese.
Top with remaining spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Fry bacon and sausage.
Drain well.
Combine meats and cheese. Spread in pie shell.
Sprinkle with onions and lay on green peppers.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over pie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix together sugar, buttermilk and soda.
Cook until it makes a soft ball in cool water or until it reaches 236° on a candy thermometer.
Then add vanilla and pecans.
Mix. Drop from a tablespoon on waxed paper.
Work fast as possible as it cools fast and the last ones will not be smooth.
Cook in large pan as the buttermilk and soda foams up and is likely to boil over.

title: caramel-pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch jelly-roll pan. To prepare cookie base:
In a large mixing bowl beat butter, brown sugar, vanilla and salt until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour 1/2 cup at a time, blending well after each addition.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Cover solidly with rows of pecan halves.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: sweet tooth treats
directions: In a bowl, combine peanut butter, corn syrup, sugar and coconut until blended. Stir in cereal. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. In small saucepan over medium heat, melt chocolate chips and shortening. Dip balls halfway into chocolate; place on wax paper-lined baking sheets to harden. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: baked raccoon and sweet potatoes
directions: Boil raccoon until tender, about 2 hours.
Remove from liquid and drain.
Put in a rectangular baking dish and season well with salt and pepper.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and blend well. Set aside. Combine beef with egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup of the soup mixture. Shape into 6 patties.
Brown patties in skillet. Drain drippings from pan. Combine remaining soup mixture and 1/2 cup water and pour over patties.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: basic macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rinse with cold water. For dressing, mix salad dressing, sour cream, milk, relish and salt. Toss dressing with macaroni mixture. Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours. Stir in additional milk, if necessary.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Dissolve salt and sugar in the milk.
Add the oil and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup of lukewarm water.
Mix the yeast and water mixture with the milk mixture. Add lightly beaten eggs.
Add half of flour and beat.
Add the remaining half of the flour and knead.
Let rise until it's doubled.
Then shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: betty's potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil until done (approximately 25 minutes).
Boil eggs with potatoes.
Remove eggs to cool.
Drain potatoes.
Add ingredients, one at a time as listed and mix with fork.
(Don't mash potatoes.)
Peel and chop eggs; stir in.
Best if served hot, but it is good refrigerated, too.

title: holiday orange salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving syrup; add enough water to syrup to make 2 cups liquid.
Place liquid in saucepan; bring to boil. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin.
Add sherbet, stirring until dissolved.
Chill until thick.
Stir in oranges.
Pour into a 2 quart ring mold; chill until firm.
Wrap in moisture proof paper; freeze.
Unwrap and thaw in refrigerator.

title: foil sandwiches
directions: Thoroughly mix together the ham, bacon, chili sauce and relish.
Mixing by hand is easiest.
Butter the insides, top and bottom of the buns.
Place a slice of cheese in each bun.
Fill buns with ham mixture.
Wrap each sandwich in foil.
Heat sandwiches in a 250° oven for 30 minutes.
(Sandwiches can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Increase heating time if refrigerated.)

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
When mixture is blended well. Fold in nuts. Pour into baking pan, 13 x 9-inch, and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Check after 45 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute vegetables for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add mayonnaise.
Butter a casserole dish.
Layer buttered croutons and mushroom mixture.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Top with grated cheese the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: garlicy bread soup
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium heat, add the olive oil.
When the oil is hot, add the onions, garlic, crushed bay leaf and crushed red pepper.
Season with salt.
Saute until slightly caramelized, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in the stock.
Bring the liquid up to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and simmer for 40 minutes.
Turn the heat up and whisk in the bread and cream. Continue whisking until the bread has dissolved into the soup, about 10 minutes.
With a handheld blender, puree the soup until smooth.
Whisk in the Parmigiana-Reggiano cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into individual soup bowls and serve.
Garnish with parsley.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: linguine and white clam sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic.
Add bottled clam juice and juice from the canned clams.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer.
Add oregano, parsley, peppers, marjoram, lemon juice and grated cheese.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Throw clams in and simmer 15 minutes.
Boil and cook linguine; top with sauce.

title: jay's stuff
directions: Stir-fry vegetables a few minutes in grease or oil.
Add seasonings.
Cook until done.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and 2 tablespoons flour, tossing to coat fruit.
Add 1 cup sugar, mixing well.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Combine oatmeal, chopped pecans, 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar; add butter and stir well.
Spoon over fruit mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with pecan halves and cranberries.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients except breadcrumbs.
Stir well; cover and chill 8 hours.
Ladle into serving bowl; sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add both cans of condensed
milk	and
continue
mixing.	Add
milk and vanilla extract.
When
all
ingredients are thoroughly mixed, pour into freezer, using either electric or hand mixer.

title: healthy muffins
directions: Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed hot peppers(canning recipe)
directions: Core peppers (don't break), wearing rubber gloves.
Wash and boil 2 minutes.
Cool in ice water.
Stuff with sauerkraut.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Add garlic and alum.
Cover with solution of water, vinegar and salt.
Boil in hot bath for 3 to 5 minutes. Seal.

title: mexican cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not use beaters.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: food for the gods
directions: Preheat stove to 350°.
Grease and line a 13 x 9 x 2 rectangular pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Take 1/2 cup of this mixture and dredge dates.
Set aside.
Cream butter until soft and fluffy.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in the flour mixture and dates into the creamed mixture.
Add walnuts.
Stir to completely blend batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes more.
Cool slightly, then cut into bars.
Individually wrap in cellophane, if desired.

title: what's today's salad
directions: Put all fruit on lettuce leaves.
Top with chives and favorite dressing.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Cook in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Leaving cake in pan, pour Eagle Brand milk, cream of coconut (mix cream of coconut well) and crushed pineapple (including juice) over cake.
Let cake cool, then top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut; decorate with cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crusty, crunchy salmon croquettes
directions: Remove bones and skin
from salmon and flake with fork. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Add milk and
egg
and
beat until smooth.
Fold salmon into this batter
and
drop by tablespoons into hot oil and fry until golden brown,
about
or 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve with ketchup or your favorite sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and coconut in bowl.
Mix sugar, milk, oleo and flavoring
in saucepan.
Bring to boil and let boil slowly for one minute.
Remove
from heat and pour over dry mixture. Stir well. Drop by spoon on waxed paper and cool.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and lemon
juice on high speed for 5 minutes.
Then add flour and spices.
Beat slightly.
Spread into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Top with 1 cup finely chopped nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at end, roll towel and cake together.
Leave until cool.

title: beans and biscuits
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Stir in brown sugar, pork and beans, salt and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

title: meat glop
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Serve with Fritos or carrot sticks.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Press mixture over apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: upside-down chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour in an oblong baking pan.
In a separate bowl mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Pour this mixture around in cake mix.
Bake according to directions on cake mix.
Cake will be very moist.
Top with icing when cooled.

title: red apple slaw
directions: Combine apples, cabbage and raisins.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream; add to cabbage mixture.
Toss until well blended. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, soup and sour cream together.
Put in baking dish. Crumble up crackers; add butter to crackers.
Sprinkle over corn mix.
Put sliced almonds on top.
Bake in oven at 250° until bubbles; remove.

title: pecan balls or coconut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and mix.
Add pecans and mix until very stiff.
Roll out into balls about 1 inch or less in diameter.
Place in waxed paper and cover.
Let sit for 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Boil chicken in water with chicken broth cubes for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and brown in skillet over medium heat in hot margarine.
Cook 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, broth or milk and pepper; heat to boiling.
Add broccoli; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender and chicken is done, stirring occasionally.

title: 3 cheese lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream the shortening.
Blend in sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well until fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternating with bananas and liquid, beating after each addition.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and cool several hours or overnight before slicing.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Combine juice with brown sugar, cornstarch, cider vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and bouillon cube.
Stir until smooth; set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and roll in a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Arrange in a tube pan.
Melt over low heat, the butter, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon.
Pour over biscuit quarters and bake at 350° until golden brown.
(Bread will spring back when lightly touched.)

title: mary's strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually add peel and sugar.
Add egg yolks to butter mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter.
Pour batter into an 8-inch greased and floured round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Mix strawberries, liqueur and sugar.
Set aside.
When cake is done, let cool 15 minutes.
Turn onto a platter or cake plate.
Cut into two layers.
Scoop ice cream onto first layer.
Top with strawberry mixture and add second layer.
Garnish with whipped cream and strawberries.
Sprinkle with orange peel.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Blend milk and egg; add to dry ingredients.
Stir in corn.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil; fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: mashed potatoes supreme
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small pieces.
Cook until tender. Drain.
Mash with butter, salt, pepper, and onion salt to taste. Cream cheese can be softened by leaving out for 1 hour, so it reaches room temperature, or in the microwave on defrost.
Be very careful not to get it hot!
Add cream cheese and sour cream to mashed potato mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place in large casserole dish, cover.
Place in oven for one half hour or until hot.
(May also heat in microwave on half power until hot.)
Stir.
Top with pat of butter or margarine. Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Serve.

title: smoked salmon cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll in chopped nuts, grated cheese or crushed crackers.
Chill.

title: cheesy brat stew
directions: Brown bratwurst lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until done.
This is about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar and sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with grated cheese; add cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Pour over casserole.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a flat pan.
Punch holes in top with end of wooden spoon.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and caramel; pour over cake.
Cool.
Spread cake with Cool Whip.
Top with crushed Butterfinger bar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in pie crust at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pie doesn't shake in middle.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook meat and suet together until pink is gone.
Add all other ingredients; cook 2 or more hours.
Freeze in family size containers and use as needed.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in one of the cups of water; add the other cup of water. Put in refrigerator 2 hours before serving. Knead, roll and cut out biscuits. Let rise and bake at 400° until brown.

title: smoky beef dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese until fairly smooth.
Add beef, onion, parsley and pepper.
Blend well.
Serve with crisp vegetables such as carrot, green pepper and celery sticks.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook meat in frying pan until it loses red color; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes; stir as needed.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook macaroni in boiling water following package directions.
Drain.
Combine macaroni and cottage cheese.
Pour a little meat mixture in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half of macaroni mixture; half the Cheddar cheese and half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle Parmesan on top and bake for 40 minutes or until well heated.
Remove from oven and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wyoming whopper cookies
directions: If using another brand of peanut butter, add several tablespoons of water to mixture.
In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add oats, baking soda, raisins and chocolate chips (dough will be sticky).
Drop on greased baking sheet using large spoon. Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: deer jerky
directions: Slice the venison into 3/8-inch thick strips to ensure total saturation of the meat when it is marinating.
Stir the remaining ingredients well.
Place meat in marinade.
Be sure the meat is covered with the liquid.
Turn, if necessary.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Lay strips on racks of oven. Cook for 6 to 8 hours at 150° or use microwave for 20 minutes.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk. Add crabmeat, Swiss cheese, onion, pepper, mushrooms and bacon.
Put in a pastry shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: In a pot, make sauce with the onion, garlic, basil, oregano, Italian seasoning, tomatoes, water, soup and cheese.
Cook spaghetti slightly; drain. Add to sauce.
Serve with tossed salad and hot garlic bread.
Enjoy.

title: chili dip
directions: Spray frying pan with Pam.
Saute beef and drain. Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add cheese and stir until melted. If too thick, add water.
Keep hot. Serve with chips.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: easy baked fish
directions: Cut fish into serving portions.
Place in a single layer in well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, green onion and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over fish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: finger rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on both sides of rolls. Add layer of ham and Swiss cheese.
Wrap in foil and heat in a 350° oven about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and coffee creamer together.
Fold mix into Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill for at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water and Crisco oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and nuts; pour into 3 x 8 or 9-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Put crock-pot full of thinly sliced apples.
Cook on high for 2 hours with lid on.
Drain off liquid.
Mash or puree apples. Add sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Stir and cook on low with lid off for at least 2 more hours.
Put at once in jars and seal.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Crumble and keep in plastic bag in refrigerator.
One cup of this makes a pie crust.

title: microwave oven fudge
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir in vanilla (and nuts if desired) and pour into greased pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour a small amount of oil into 10-inch iron skillet; heat in oven.
Add ingredients to cornmeal in order that they are listed.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour in iron skillet and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Mix.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian skillet supper
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and pepper in a 10-inch skillet; drain.
Combine oats and egg in bowl and mix until oats are coated.
Add oats to meat mixture; cook over medium heat about 3 minutes or until oats are dry, separated and lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Add combined tomato sauce, water, seasoned salt, pepper, garlic salt and oregano; continue cooking for 5 minutes or until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in crust; chill.

title: holiday relish
directions: Quarter oranges and seed.
Leave peeling on oranges.
Chop or grind cranberries, oranges and pecans.
Add sugar and blend. Refrigerate in covered bowl for at least 4 hours before serving. Can be frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great for the holidays.

title: yeast rolls(makes about 15 to 18 rolls)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil, egg and water.
Mix well.
Place in covered bowl and place in refrigerator.
Remove as much as needed.
Knead on floured board. Roll 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Let rise 1 or 2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: sara's watergate strawberry salad
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese; add pineapple and juice.
Blend strawberries and bananas together until smooth, then add to cream cheese mixture along with nuts and Cool Whip.
Freeze in baking cups and keep in freezer until serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside. Beat eggs.
Add vegetable oil and walnuts.
Add beaten eggs, oil and nuts to thawed strawberries with juice.
Blend this strawberry mixture into the dry ingredients, without beating.
Blend only with a rubber spatula.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool on rack in pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove.
Cut when completely cooled.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
With an electric mixer, beat egg whites until stiff not dry.
Gradually beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla; fold in pecans.
Drop teaspoonful of dough 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until firm. Cookies should remain light.
Remove from sheet at once.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Dip chicken parts in egg, then matzo meal and brown.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Mix preserves, horseradish, sugar and salt and heat until bubbly.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Re-baste.
Put one pineapple chunk on each breast (optional) and bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: doo dads
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Add dates and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: corned beef and cabbage sandwiches
directions: On
4 slices of pumpernickel bread, spread mustard-mayonnaise sauce.
Top
with lettuce, Swiss cheese, corned beef, red
cabbage and
remaining
bread slices.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: buffet baked beans and franks
directions: Mix beans, onion, garlic, brown sugar and mustard until blended.
Split frankfurters lengthwise and fill with pineapple chunks.
Pour beans into a shallow baking dish.
Press frankfurters on top of beans.
Drizzle with bacon drippings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot artichoke dip(preparation time:  10 minutes; cooking time:  25 minutes)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow ovenproof dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onions and chopped tomatoes, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers or assorted cocktail bread slices.
Makes 2 cups.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together (with your hands) the first 5 ingredients until you can form it into a big ball.
Spray Pam or grease a large cooking pan.
Turn meat onto wax paper or into the pan. Flatten out like a big square burger.
Spread the cheese along the top of the flattened meat. Spread the rice across the meat and cheese.
Take both ends of the flattened meat and turn them towards the center.
Shape it the best you can to cover all rice and cheese with meat.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. If not done, continue cooking until done, checking every 30 minutes.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar and egg and pour into casserole. Top with the cubed bread.
