Moisten bread slightly with juices from pineapple mixture without stirring.
Spoon slid down along side works well.

title: green salad
directions: Make as you would milk gravy, just add a small can of diced tomatoes and mix well.
For more tomato taste, mash chunks of tomato; mix well.
This is great on homemade biscuits and fried potatoes.

title: democrat jackass stew
directions: Cut Jackass in 1-inch cubes (this takes about 1 week, unless you are extra slow).
Season and place in a large wash tub casserole with vegetables.
Bake for 6 days at 425°.
This serves 1,200 people.
For larger crowds, you can add 2 rabbits, however some people object to hare in their stew.

title: fluffy meringue
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: one egg cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add the sugar, vanilla and egg to the butter.
Stir in half the flour mixture and 1/4 cup milk. Add the rest of the flour mixture and milk.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Makes one 8 x 8-inch layer or 12 cupcakes.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Use a large casserole dish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken and pepper in 2 quarts of water, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken.

title: vidalia onion casserole(or 10 to 15 casserole)
directions: Spray casserole dish with oil spray or oil dish.
Cover bottom of dish thickly with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Melt butter in skillet. Saute onion rings, then remove to casserole dish with drippings. Salt and pepper lightly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until hot.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix other ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour 1/2 mixture in casserole dish and crumble 1/2 potato chips on it.
Add other 1/2 mixture and cover with the rest of the potato chips.
Bake in hot oven about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter and crush crackers for topping.
Place on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Peel, pit and slice peaches into already baked pie crust.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil until clear, approximately 1 minute.
Stir entire time.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 tablespoons peach jello.
Pour over fruit and chill well before serving.

title: tamale pie
directions: Unwrap tamales and dispose of wrappers.
Cut tamales into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces and place a layer on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cover with a layer of Fritos.
Pour over a layer of chili. Continue until all is used up ending with a layer of chili.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: dried apples and cinnamon cut-outs part 1(non edible)
directions: Mix warm applesauce and cinnamon together to form a ball. Sprinkle a board with additional cinnamon.
Roll mixture out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes using a cookie cutter.
Use a pencil to punch a hole in the top of each shape if it is to be used as an ornament.
Place cut-outs into a 150° oven for 6 hours.

title: cevapici
directions: Season ground lamb with salt and pepper to taste. Shape meat into cylinders 1 1/2 to 2-inches long. Refrigerate overnight. Cook meat on charcoal or wood grill, turning until done. Toast pita rounds until slightly brown but still flexible. Fill each half with meat.
Top with chopped onion.
Makes 12 pita pockets.

title: tuna rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil; boil 10 minutes on low flame.
Serve hot.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In large bowl combine first 3 ingredients.
Blend at low speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Place 2 3/4 cups of crumb mixture into an ungreased, 13 x 9-inch pan.
To the remaining mixture, add cinnamon, salt, soda, sour cream, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon evenly over crumb layer in pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cut in squares.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Yield:
12 to 15 squares.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Beat.
Mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, cocoa and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: In a small bowl, blend first 5 ingredients.
Add and blend well the remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch shell and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 25 more minutes.

title: garlic herb butter
directions: Soften oleo and stir in remaining ingredients.
Use to make garlic bread; put on chicken.
Cook 1 cup spiral pasta according to package directions and drain well.
Put into serving bowl or dish.
Add 2 tablespoons or more to taste and toss well to coat pasta.

title: egg bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Add egg yolks to buttermilk and stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased black iron skillet.
Bake at 400 degrees 25 minutes or until brown.

title: mama's dressing
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and cube.
Cook onion, celery and green pepper in 1 cup chicken stock.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and turn into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Freeze well too.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: walnut frosties
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Form dough into 1 inch balls. Make depression in the center. Fill with topping.

title: beef with broccoli
directions: Put beef slices and add soy sauce, cornstarch, salt, pepper, wine, broth, ginger, sugar, onions into a big bowl until smooth. Set aside for 20 minutes at least (they can be marinated up to 24 hours.
Sealed and covered in refrigerator).

title: chewy fudge-cake cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and oil in a saucepan.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to chocolate mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Then with damp hands, form into balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Add the shortening, sugar and egg together; stir well.
Add the flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Stir in the vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 or 10 minutes.

title: fudge clusters
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa and milk together until dissolved.
Bring to boil and boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until butters have melted.
Add oatmeal. Drop on waxed paper.
Enjoy!

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water until frothy (not stiff). Stir in sugar, salt and cinnamon. Mix well. Add pecans and stir until all are coated and spread on large baking sheet and bake and stir every 15 minutes. When cool, store in airtight container.
So good.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over bottom of pan.
Spoon batter over coconut and pecans.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, cover the raisins with water and cook them over medium-high heat until they are very plump and tender. Drain the raisins; return them to the saucepan. To the raisins, add the sour cream and boil for 10 minutes. To the sour cream and raisins, add the sugar, flour, egg yolks, vanilla and salt. Cook until thick, then add the pecans and remove from heat. Pour the mixture into a prebaked pie shell; top with meringue made from left over whites and 4 tablespoons of sugar. Bake in a 350° oven until the meringue is brown.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and garlic and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Repeat with another layer of crackers, the remaining pudding and another layer of crackers.
Add icing to last layer of crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and cheese sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Drain chicken; reserve broth.
Mix chicken, spinach and 1/4 cup cheese.
Top each muffin with onion and 1/4 of the chicken mixture.
Mix broth and milk.
Combine with remaining cheese, egg and mustard.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: pink and perky punch
directions: Add ingredients in order written and you have the perfect pink and perky punch!

title: noodle hamburger casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onion and hamburger; brown lightly. Cook noodles; drain.
Add browned meat to noodles.
Stir in tomato soup, water, grated cheese and seasoning.
Pour into greased casserole at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Press with a fork before baking.
You may wish to add food coloring for special holidays.

title: heart smart cocoa cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
At high speed, gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at one time.
At low speed, beat in cocoa and extract.
Fold in almonds.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until set.
Cool on sheets. Remove to wire rack.
Makes about 25 cookies.

title: shrimp, asparagus and basil spaghetti sauce
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Cover lightly with foil in an ovenproof bowl and keep warm in oven. While spaghetti is cooking, make the sauce.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix well and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
You may refrigerate this overnight if necessary.
Add 7-Up when ready to serve.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 gallons.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 9-inch pan stir together vegetable oil and potatoes.
Press evenly into pie crust shape.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Layer on cheese, meat and onion.
In a bowl beat together milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Pie is done when knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed, but add lemon curd and use 1/4 cup less water.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.

title: green tomato-apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
To peel tomatoes easily, place in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes until skins slip off easily.
Combine tomatoes, apple, brown and granulated sugars, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Place in 9-inch pie plate lined with 1 pastry crust.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and flute edges.
Cut vents for steam.
Bake in preheated oven 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute
onion
in butter until slightly brown.
Put that with rest
of
the ingredients in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: party rye-finger food
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread on cocktail rye or party rye bread (2 loaves).
Broil and serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Prepare pastry; roll 2/3 dough into 14-inch square roll, remaining dough into 14 x 7-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2 squares. Place an apple on each square.
Mix raisins and nuts; fill center of each apple.
Moisten corners of square; bring 2 opposite corners of pastry up over apple and press together.
Fold in sides of remaining corners.
Bring corners up over apple and press together.
Place dumplings in ungreased baking dish.
Heat brown sugar and water to boiling.
Pour around dumplings.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 425°.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let set for 3 hours; drain well. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: ratatouille
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender, then salt and pepper to taste.
Excellent frozen.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together with wire whisk and let set.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken breast into four strips per breast.
Spread rice in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on rice.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
Serve with a garden salad.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, form into a ball and refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add soda, salt, flour and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoons into greased cookie sheet.
(Makes large cookies.)
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.
Remove as soon as set.
Only bake 1 sheet at a time in the center of the oven.

title: party potatoes
directions: In
large
bowl,
combine
potatoes,
sour cream, cream cheese, chives and garlic powder.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine
bread
crumbs with butter;
sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve immediately.
Dish can be assembled a day ahead and baked just before serving.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, egg, peanut butter and flour together. Place far apart because they will spread; mash down with fork, crisscrossing. Bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: cornflake crunchies
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, Karo and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and boil about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir well, then pour in cornflakes.
Mix well, then drop tablespoonfuls onto greased wax paper or foil.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook and stir celery, mushrooms and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in parsley, salt and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Trim fat from pork chops.
Make a slit in each to form a pocket.
Fill pocket with celery mixture.
Dip each pork chop into mixture of eggs and milk.
Roll in mixture of 3/4 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the paprika.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes; turn pork chops over.
Bake about 15 minutes or until pork chops are tender.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring to boil the salt and water; stir in grits and follow the package directions.
Turn off heat.
Add butter, milk, garlic powder and 1 1/2 cups of the shredded Cheddar cheese, mixing well. Let cool so that eggs will not cook when added.
Add eggs and pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
During last few minutes of baking, sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top of the casserole.

title: andre's favorite fried turkey wings
directions: Season and boil turkey wings until well done; let cool.
Heat shortening while battering turkey wings in flour.
When the shortening is hot, place turkey wings in the hot pan of shortening and fry each turkey wing for about 2 minutes.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and powdered sugar.
Cake can be frosted hot out of the oven.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken pieces in melted butter.
Combine bread crumbs, parsley, garlic and cheese.
Roll chicken in this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good served with French green beans, Caesar salad and Vienna bread.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil and chicken.
Stir in dressing.
Mix to coat chicken. brown chicken.
Add 16 ounces vegetable oil and 2 tablespoons water.
Stir 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fajita pizza
directions: Brush both sides (top and bottom) of the pizza crust with olive oil.
Set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in olive oil until tender.
Set aside.
Cut chicken tenders into small pieces and saute in olive oil; sprinkle with fajita seasoning while cooking.
Spread salsa evenly onto pizza crust.
Top with peppers and onions.
Next, spread chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with more fajita seasoning.
Cover with Monterey Jack cheese.
Place pizza directly on oven racks in a preheated 450° oven and bake until golden brown.
Watch carefully.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine all of your ingredients, except the biscuits and the melted butter, in a small dish.
Take your biscuits and dip them into the melted butter and then into your other ingredients. Place them in together in a Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh vegetables with horseradish-mustard dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
(Can be prepared 2 days ahead.)
Place dip in center of platter. Surround with assorted vegetables (such as carrots, celery, cucumber, bell pepper strips, snow peas, endive spears and cherry tomatoes).

title: pie crust
directions: Place the flour, sugar and salt in the pie pan and mix with your fingers until blended.
In a measuring cup, combine oil and milk and beat with a fork until creamy; pour all at once over the flour mixture.
Mix with fork until flour mixture is completely moistened.
Pat the dough with your fingers, first up the sides of the pan, then across bottom.
Flute the edges.
Shell is ready to be filled.
If you are preparing a shell to fill later, preheat the oven to 425°.
Prick the surface of the pastry with a fork and bake 15 minutes.
Check often, pricking if needed.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Peel and remove seeds from cucumbers.
Grate and blot on paper towels along with grated onion.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: Cook the water or water and milk, bouillon cubes, raw potatoes, onions and celery for 20 minutes, then add the frozen broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook for 10 minutes, then add the soup and cheese.

title: fantastic dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix sugar, flour and nuts. Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients except for the crackers and cheese.
Crumble the crackers and spread 1/2 cup of the crumbs over the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put mixture into dish and sprinkle cracker crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Spoon over hot biscuits or toast to serve.

title: squash dish
directions: Place margarine and carrots in large skillet.
Cook until half done.
Add rest of ingredients, except tomatoes.
Cook until tender.
Do not overcook.
Squeeze juice out of tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and hot sauce to mixture and cook for 1 additional minute.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Melt cheese.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot; let simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Scald milk; let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in the cooled milk.
Add 2 cups of flour; beat for 5 minutes.
Add melted shortening and beat for 1 minute.
Add the cups of flour and salt.
Turn onto board with 1 cup flour; knead well.
Cover; let rise for 30 minutes.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and bake (no need to knead the second time; just punch down and make into rolls).

title: fried ramps
directions: Pull off outer skin of ramps to clean them.
Chop ramps fine and fry in an iron skillet in bacon grease, adding salt to taste. When done, break eggs into ramps and scramble them.
Cook until done.
For a milder taste, substitute chopped green onions for ramps in this recipe.

title: cracker brittle
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Arrange crackers on pan.
In small saucepan, combine butter and sugar. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour and spread over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Break into pieces.

title: pixie pie
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch baking dish.
Coat berries with 1 cup of sugar.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in milk gradually; beat well.
Pour batter into melted butter and mix lightly.
Pour berries in pan, spreading them evenly over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Berries will sink into batter while baking. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: turtles
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave about 90 seconds; stir well. Continue to melt in microwave in 15 second intervals until completely melted, stirring well.
After melted, place on top of boiler of heated water.
Melt caramel in microwave about 1 minute, only enough so that you may stir it.
Do not overheat! Mix caramel and pecans together to form little patties or balls, whichever you prefer.
Using a fork, dip the caramel and pecans into the chocolate and drop on aluminum foil.
Cool completely. Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: olive cheese nuggets
directions: Blend
cheese and butter.
Sift flour, salt and paprika into that mixture.
Shape around olives using about a teaspoon of dough for each.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbled.
Drain excess. In crock-pot, melt cheese.
Add meat, soup, tomatoes, green chilies and onions; mix well.
Makes a large amount and can be frozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, 1/2 of the sugar and melted margarine.
In another bowl, mix cocoa and flour with just enough hot water to dissolve sugar.
Add chocolate mixture to egg mixture and stir well.
Add vanilla and salt, stirring well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Top with whipped cream and almond slivers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine milk, flour and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add to the melted margarine. Add peaches and do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream, if desired.
(Canned or frozen peaches may be substituted for fresh.)

title: mandarin shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp.
When cool enough to handle, peel and remove tails.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water until it reaches a hard-crack stage.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Spray a cookie sheet or mini ice cube tray with Pam.
Pour hot liquid into this.
Cool and crack.
Shake pieces in powdered sugar.
Use caution; very hot.

title: hay stacks
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler.
Mix in marshmallows and chow mein noodles.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: boiled cake(grandpa's favorite)
directions: Mix sugar, raisins, coffee, shortening, cinnamon, baking soda, cloves and nutmeg in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt into cooled mixture in saucepan.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Spread mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Serve each slice topped with applesauce and whipped cream.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until firm.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together pineapple, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add instant pudding.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie in orange shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Cut the top fourth off each orange; then hollow oranges with a grapefruit spoon or a melon baller. Blend the scooped orange together with the remaining ingredients; then fill each orange shell with the mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes or until juice begins to run from the oranges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lite mac-n-cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients (except 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese).
Add macaroni.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: belgium:  beef and beer
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge the meat in the seasoned flour.
Heat the oil in skillet; add onions and garlic until tender but not brown.
Remove from skillet and reserve.
Put meat in the skillet and brown on all sides, adding a little more oil if necessary.
Put meat, onions, beer, bay leaf and thyme in a casserole; cover and put in a preheated 325° oven for three hours or more until meat is tender.
Remove from oven; remove bay leaf and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with hot boiled potatoes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch sheet pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook peeled apples to a sauce, using as little water as possible.
Fill crock-pot 3/4 full, adding ingredients as listed. Cook 8 to 10 hours on high.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: cabbage pickles
directions: Chop cabbage and onions fine.
Add vinegar and boil for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix seasonings with flour adding enough water to make a paste.
Stir paste into boiling pickles and boil for 20 minutes.
Bottle and seal while hot.

title: kay's chicken almond
directions: Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons butter. Add ginger. Bring to boil. Add rice and soup mix. Boil 1 minute. Add all other ingredients. Mix well and pour into large casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10 to 20, depending if served alone or on buffet with other main dishes.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Dust paprika and black pepper over wieners.
Pour mixture over wieners, split lengthwise in baking dish.
Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven until tender.

title: deviled egg and broccoli casserole
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks and mash with remaining ingredients, except broccoli.
Fill eggs with stuffing. Arrange drained broccoli in baking dish and place eggs on top. Pour Cheese Sauce over all and top with bread crumbs.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cut strips of floured tortillas, size of about 3-inches wide. Mix tomatoes, soup and sour cream together in blender or mix real well.
Layer like lasagna the tortilla strips, chicken and cottage cheese; repeat for second layer, then add sauce to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set for awhile before eating.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a covered jar.
Place 2 teaspoons in cup of hot water to serve.
Yield:
25 to 30 servings.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: braised oxtail
directions: Wash and clean cut up oxtail.
Season with salt and garlic powder.
Coat with flour and fry until brown.
Put in a roaster; add chicken broth and bake in 350° oven until meat separates from bone.
Cool and serve.
Finger licking good!

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Heat sugar and syrup to boiling point; pour over peanut butter crunch and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add Special K cereal.
Press in buttered pan.
Melt both packages of chips and pour over mixture.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar when still hot or cool and spread with icing.
(Children love this cookie when you use several colors for icing.)

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Toss cucumbers with salt.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, onion, sugar and pepper; blend well.
Reserve 1/4 cup of mixture.
Combine cucumbers with remainder of the sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate until well chilled, about 2 hours.
To serve, place remainder of mixture over top for garnish.

title: coney island dogs
directions: Cook hot dogs.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add sour cream, flour, soda and lemon extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.
Let cool 10 minutes before turning out.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pull cooled chicken from bone in small pieces and mix with soup and sour cream.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread crackers on mixture.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken n' dressing
directions: Mix dressing mix with melted margarine.
Put 2/3 of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix in bottom of large casserole dish.
Layer chicken, soup and stock.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 300° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture; beat well. Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter. Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal. Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: mincemeat bread stuffing(for turkey or chicken)
directions: Toast bread cubes until slightly crisp.
Add mincemeat, salt, pepper and butter.
Toss lightly with 2 forks until well blended. Use to stuff chicken or turkey.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In large bowl, combine mixed nuts and butter; set aside. In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients; stir into nut mixture. On ungreased baking sheet, evenly spread nut mixture. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until nuts are golden. Great for holiday appetizers and homemade snack gifts!

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: oyster ritz
directions: Mix oil, garlic and dill weed well.
Put oyster crackers in bowl with lid.
Pour oil mixture over crackers.
Cover and shake well.
Refrigerate at least overnight.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; add 1/2 cup pecans (more if desired). Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 35 minutes more. Use an unbaked pie shell.

title: skillet squash
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse the beans.
In a large Dutch oven cover beans with the 6 cups water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 1 hour.
(Or soak beans in water overnight in a covered pan.)
Drain and rinse beans.

title: fruit dip
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar.
Remove and stir in vanilla and sour cream.
Fix the night or day before to thicken. Suggested fruit to dip:
Bananas, apples, strawberries and pineapple.

title: zucchini bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 to 15 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
In small bowl, blend egg, milk and oil; stir in 100% bran.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, walnuts and cinnamon; mix until well combined.
Stir into flour mixture just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In large kettle, cook vegetables in water until tender. Drain, reserving liquid. Set vegetables aside.

title: martini
directions: Over cracked ice in cocktail shaker, pour gin and vermouth. Stir.
Strain mixture into 2 chilled cocktail glasses.
Garnish with either olives or lemon twists.

title: chicken baked in sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange four 12-inch squares of foil on baking sheet.
Blend garlic salt, celery seed and sour cream.
Dip chicken in butter, sour cream and then crumbs.
Arrange each in square foil to form sealed package.
Bake for 1 hour.
Open foil and bake 15 minutes longer or when chicken is brown.

title: favorite dinner muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups, or spray with Pam cooking spray. Beat egg whites, stir in oil and milk. Mix in flour until just moistened.
Batter should be lumpy. Fill cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Immediately remove from pan.
**NOTE: To make sweeter muffins, increase sugar to 1/2 cup and for variety, add 1 cup fresh, well-drained blueberries.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, cabbage and onion in a large bowl; mix well and set aside.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix potatoes, egg and pepper.
Pat into patties and roll lightly in flour.
Fry in hot oil until browned, turning only once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mama's mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add canned items.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan about 15 minutes at 350°. Will be a thin layer.
Beat cream cheese, pudding mix and milk together.
Spread over cake.
Spoon pineapple over pudding mixture.
Cover all with whipped topping.
Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until fluffy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla until it is thick and lemon colored.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert on rack and let cool completely.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli. Combine sugar and mayonnaise and add to vegetables. Add crisp bacon; mix well. Refrigerate covered overnight.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes, or until water is absorbed.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Let yeast, 2 tablespoons sugar and warm water stand until dissolved.
Combine eggs, salt and 2/3 cup sugar; beat well. Scald milk and add shortening.
Stir until shortening is melted. Cool.
Combine yeast mixture, milk mixture and egg mixture.
Stir in flours and mix well.
(Mixer can be used.)
Place in large bowl and let rise until double in size.
Knead down and roll on floured surface to about 2/3-inch thick.
Cut into rolls with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted margarine. Let rise at room temperature for 2 hours.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions under water.
Slice in bowl of milk.
Let stand 15 minutes. Drain. Beat eggs.
Add salt, pepper, milk and flour to make smooth batter. Dip onions in batter and drop in deep hot fat or dip onions in flour and fry.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: saucy asparagus
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine the soup and milk.
Heat until it boils.
Add asparagus.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until asparagus is tender.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: tomato-onion-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling the oil, vinegar and salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: In a 2 cup microwave-safe bowl, cook chocolate pieces and shortening on 100% power or High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in nuts, noodles or marshmallows.
Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper.
Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 18 pieces.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients with enough water to hold together.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° (about 15 minutes) until golden brown. May be frozen and reheated.

title: sweet trash
directions: Mix white Karo, butter and brown sugar together and melt in microwave. Mix Crispix, pretzels and nuts together in large bowl, then pour into a greased large baking sheet.

Pour sugar mixture over and toss well to coat. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. When ready, as soon as cool enough to handle, put in gallon Ziploc bags and toss until cool to keep from sticking. Lie flat.

title: mother's cracker dumplings
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients in food grinder.
Add milk and oleo; heat until oleo melts.
Combine with cracker mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Cook in chicken broth
7 to 10 minutes.
Add to your favorite chicken stew.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl with dressing.
Add Fritos just before eating.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no-stick spray.
Dip chicken in margarine and coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Makes 6 servings at 270 calories each.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add milk, flour, spices, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 3 x 8-inch layer pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: arkansas baked beans
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper together.
Saute ground beef until done, but not brown.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients. Pour into bean pot or other casserole type dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pastel de choclo
directions: Drain the corn and cook at low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the milk slowly; it must be creamy.
Add salt and pepper.

title: life like cookie dough
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill slightly.
Roll out on floured surface; cut in desired shapes.
Decorate before or after.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients. Serve on rye bread or crackers.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Mix together and fry until desired brownness over medium heat.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or with rye or pumpernickel round.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo together 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix in peanut butter, vanilla and cooking oats.
Let cool a few minutes.
Drop from a teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: baked chicken
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Dip pieces of chicken in egg and milk mixture.
Roll in crumbs.
Place in well greased baking dish using butter or oleo.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle with poultry seasoning.
Bake at 325 until meat loosens from bone.

title: chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: Dip chicken in egg whites, then coat with bread crumbs.
Cook chicken in skillet until tender.
Add soup, milk and water.
Serve over rice.

title: bunt bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and 3/4 c. of the sugar in a plastic bag and shake. Cut biscuits into quarters and add to bag and shake.
Place into ungreased Bunt pan. In saucepan bring butter, remaining sugar, brown sugar to a boil. Mix pecans pour over biscuits. Let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 min.
Remove from pan immediately after cooked.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Put 1 cup sugar in cherries and let set.
Melt 1 stick butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter in pan. Spoon cherries over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until well done and set aside on warm.
Fry ground beef with onion, sauce, mushrooms and green pepper.
Add the spices and add to spaghetti and mix well.
Serve with garlic or French bread.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon, then add eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add chopped pecans last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roasted spice pecans
directions: Melt butter. Add garlic, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Spread pecans on a cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over it. Slow roast at 200° for 1 hour.
They should be shiny and tan when finished.

title: rice cakes
directions: Cook rice in boiling water until tender; drain and add beaten eggs, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Spoon into skillet of hot cooking oil.
Let brown on each side by turning.
Put on paper towels; let drain, then serve.
Serves as bread for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix
together
the broccoli (chopped), bacon, onion and raisins.
Blend
together the sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar and spread over salad mixture.

title: curried meatballs
directions: Mix beef, curry
powder, stuffing mix, salt and pepper. Shape into teaspoon size	balls
and saute in butter over high heat for 5 minutes or until brown.
Yields 32 balls.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Add flour gradually; dough will be stiff.
Fill cookie press.
Place cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender, cover and blend at high speed for 1 minute, stopping once to stir down.
Bake on greased griddle using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Makes 20 (4-inch) pancakes.
Good for waffles, also.
Bake extra and freeze.
Reheat in toaster.

title: great mexican corn bread
directions: Prepare corn bread according to instructions on Jiffy mix box. Fry/saute onion (chopped); combine cooked onion pieces, 1 can of creamed corn and diced Ro-Tel tomatoes.
(If using canned Ro-Tel, drain before emptying contents.)
Mix 3/4 of cheese in with corn bread mix, onions, Ro-Tel and creamed corn.
Grease pan, 9 x 13-inch; cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Watch to see when edges turn lightly brown and it looks done.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of corn bread while hot.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Put apple slices into pie crust.
Add 3/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and margarine. Mix until crumbly and put on top of apples.
Cover with foil and bake, covered, at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and cook 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: sesame pralines
directions: Toast sesame seed in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
In 3-quart saucepan, combine both sugars and cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until dissolved.
Wash crystals from sides of pan.
Cook to 230° on candy thermometer.
Add butter, pecans and sesame seed. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, to 234° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes, then stir until thickened.
Working fast, drop from spoon onto buttered waxed paper.
Cool.

title: k.c.'s killer smoked salmon
directions: Cut salmon into small pieces.
Put remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add fish and just enough water to cover.
Soak for 8 to 12 hours.
Place on rack and let sit for 1 hour.
Pepper top of fish, if you like.
Smoke to desired consistency.

title: cream cheese desserts
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cupcake wrapper inside a muffin pan.
Pour mixture in each cup 3/4 full.
Place 3 to 4 cherries on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: rosemary grilled chicken with red pepper sauce
directions: Combine mustard and 1 tablespoon lemon juice, stirring well. Spread mustard mixture on both sides of chicken and sprinkle with pepper. Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients adding fruit last.
Pour into baking dish and bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
You can substitute any fruit, seedless grapes, pitted cherries, plums, etc.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Mash out on cookie sheet with fork to form design on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: potato rusks(bread rolls)
directions: While hot, combine 1 cup mashed potatoes, 3/4 cup sugar and 1 cup potato water in a large bowl.
Dissolve 1 cake yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Thaw ice cream a little.
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip.
Add crushed Oreo cookies and mix slowly.
Place in serving dishes or containers to thicken.
Put in freezer for awhile before serving.

title: mexican noodles
directions: Brown onions in bacon fat or oil.
Remove onions and fry noodles and ground beef until they are brown, turning frequently. Drain excess fat.
Add onions, green peppers, tomatoes, chili powder and salt to noodles and meat.
Cover and simmer until noodles are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling. After mixed, refrigerate.
After congealed, mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and nuts.
Spread over top of congealed salad. Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: white chili
directions: Sort and wash beans. Place in Dutch oven. Cover with water 2-inches above beans; let soak 8 hours. Drain and wash beans; return to Dutch oven. Add broth and next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add chicken, chilies, cumin, oregano and cloves to bean mixture; cover and cook 30 minutes. Spoon into serving bowls. Top each with grated cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cool carrots.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over drained, cool carrots.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cheese dip
directions: Crumble hamburger meat/sausage into frying pan.
Cook until done; drain.
Add all ingredients into slow cooker or similar. Mix well and heat slowly until all the cheese has melted.
Serve with chips, tacos or vegetable tray.
Refrigerate any unused portion.
Also, leftover cheese dip tastes good cold as a cheese spread.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Roll meat in flour and brown in margarine.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, thyme, bay leaf, and water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
May also add peas.
Cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: baklava
directions: Keep phyllo leaves under a damp cloth until needed.
Using 1/2 of phyllo leaves, layer, spreading each with melted butter.
Fold leaves as necessary to fit into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the leaves and butter.
Top with remaining leaves, brushing each with melted butter.
Cut into diamond shape and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.
Honey is poured over each while they are hot.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add dates and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 325° oven for 18 minutes.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Spread ice cream evenly in bottom of crust.
Freeze until ice cream is firm.
Spread caramel sauce over ice cream; sprinkle with peanuts.
Cover with whipped topping.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 20 minutes or until pie can be easily cut.
Garnish with additional caramel sauce and peanuts. Makes 8 servings.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place 2 round layer pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inch in oven.
Beat eggs, flour, milk and salt in small mixer bowl on medium speed for 1 minute. Remove pans from oven.
Place 2 tablespoons margarine in each pan; rotate pans until margarine is melted and coats sides of pans.
Arrange half of apple slices in each pan; divide batter evenly between pans.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar mixture over batter in each pan.
Bake, uncovered, until puffed and golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: rum sauced bananas
directions: Add brown sugar and margarine to the apple juice and simmer over medium heat.
Add bananas and cook until bananas become very soft.
Add rum and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Serve over ice cream or cake.
Serves 3. Recipe doubles easily.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding milk till mixture is mixed well. You might need more or less milk depending on how you would like your batter. When everything is mixed together it should look like cornbread that is why you need to be the judge about how much milk you need. Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 - 45 minutes or until done.

title: brer rabbit's carrots
directions: Pare the carrots with a vegetable parer.
Cut them into thin slices.
Place the carrots in a saucepan and cover with cold water. Cover the saucepan and heat over medium-high heat until the water starts to boil Turn the heat down to low.
Remove the cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
When the carrots are tender, pour the contents of the saucepan into a colander in the sink.
(If you are a child, get help, don't do it yourself.)
Shake the colander to drain off all the water.

title: quick peach pie dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread melted margarine evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine baking mix, sugar and milk in bowl; mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into prepared dish; do not stir.
Top with peaches; do not stir.
Bake until batter rises to top and browns.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all together and place in freezer can.
Freeze according to your ice cream freezer directions.
Can be stored in refrigerator freezer and will not get too hard, but remain
just right to eat.

title: apple nobby cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Sift together the flour and all dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts; mix well.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square pan (8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until a toothpick thrust into center of cake comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Use rectangular pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut and nuts together and sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Mix stick of margarine and cream cheese together, heat until soft enough to mix.
Add powdered sugar with margarine and cream cheese.
Pour cake mix into pan, then pour mix of margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar on top.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: three week cole slaw
directions: Shred or chop cabbage.
Shred or chop onions and leave on top of cabbage (do not stir).
Bring to a boil other ingredients and pour over cabbage and onions.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Stir and serve.
Can be kept up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix together topping, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice and add bananas, pineapple, pecans and cherries.

title: microwave toffee
directions: Spread pecans evenly in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine sugar and margarine.
Microwave at High for 4 1/2 to 8 1/2 minutes, or until sugar is dissolved, stirring after 2 minutes, then every minute.
Do not overcook!
Spread mixture over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 20 seconds until chocolate is melted.
Spread chocolate over candy.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Yield:
1 pound.

title: leche quemada(caramel milk pudding)
directions: Pour milk into 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; cover with foil. Place in shallow pan; pour boiling water around it to a depth of 3/4-inch.
Bake in 425° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold.
Top with coffee liqueur and cream.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; stir in sugar, cornstarch, water, lemon juice and rind.
Cook until mixture is thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites and put meringue on top of pie.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Cook on waffle iron.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken breasts.
Tear up and place in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Crumble 1 stick Ritz crackers over.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: boston brown bread or bug bread
directions: Simmer water and raisins for 15 minutes.
Add dry ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until well blended. Add egg.
Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before taking off sheet.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a pastry blender or fork. Spread and press in a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and spread over top.
Let dry and cut in bars.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Saute onion in butter.
Put all ingredients in a pan, except sour cream.
Add crumbled bacon and cook until done.
Do not drain potatoes.
Add sour cream and let heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: arkansas chocolate gravy
directions: In iron skillet, mix together all dry ingredients.
Gradually add milk to this mixture.
Stir until completely mixed.
Cook over low heat until thickens.
If this doesn't thicken, add 1 teaspoon each sugar and cocoa plus 1 tablespoon flour.
Serve with hot buttered biscuits.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and melted butter.
Form in little balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate almond bark; put a little in bottom of aluminum cup cake and put a peanut ball on top of chocolate.
Press slightly.
Pour a little more chocolate on top. Makes 90 small cups.

title: coffee urn punch
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in coffee urn.
Layer cloves, cinnamon and salt in urn basket and perk.
Serve hot.

title: apple snack cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in pecans, half the butterscotch morsels and apples.
Spread batter (will be very stiff) into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: cowboy baked beans
directions: Saute onion and ground beef.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients. Put in deep casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven 30-40 minutes.

title: brownie cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
Let cool slightly.
Pour chocolate cake mix into pudding.
Stir well. Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before baking, put chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jerry's pink peanut patty
directions: Mix peanuts, milk, Karo, sugar and margarine. Cook until thick, forms ball, 240 degrees. Remove from heat; add vanilla and red food coloring. Beat until cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine with chopped onion.
Add all other ingredients, except shredded cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish; top with sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Stir in flour and spices alternately with water and soda mix.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Cream the cheese. Add all ingredients and mix.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package and punch holes in top. Pour Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping over cake. Then cover with Cool Whip. Crush up candy bars and put over Cool Whip.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, stock and brown sugar in a heavy saucepan with lid; bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and cover tightly.
Cook the carrots until they are about half done, 10 to 15 minutes; then remove the lid from the pot.
Return the heat to medium-low and reduce the cooking liquid to a thick syrup.
As the syrup thickens, shake the pan frequently to keep the carrots from sticking.
When the syrup is thick, add the butter, pepper, nutmeg and salt.
When the butter is melted, shake the pan again, rolling the carrots gently in the glaze so each piece is covered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: diabetic cheesecake
directions: In a medium saucepan, beat egg yolks and orange juice together. Sprinkle with gelatine.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatine is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sweetener, lemon juice and flavoring.
Pour into blender or food processor.
Cover and blend at high speed until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown together beef, chilies and onions.
Add chicken soup, cheese soup, evaporated milk, water, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Make 2 layers of chips.
Then beef mixture, then cheese in 8 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Bake in oven 30 minutes at 350° until brown and hot throughout.

title: one hour dinner rolls
directions: Crumble
yeast	in lukewarm water.
To lukewarm buttermilk, add sugar and shortening.
Sift into buttermilk mixture, flour, soda
and
salt.
Beat
smooth
by	hand.
Let stand 10 minutes. Work
and roll out dough.
Shape in rolls.	Let rise 30 minutes in warm place.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put whole strawberries in baked pie shell.
Put water, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Boil until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and stir in jello until mixed.
Pour over strawberries in pie crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except for coconut in a blender on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into 8 or 9 inch pie pan.
Let set for 5 minutes. Shake coconut over pie.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crisp lettuce.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pasta primavera(springtime pasta)
directions: Cook pasta.
Saute onion and garlic in medium skillet about 1 minute.
Add vegetables and saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in reserved tomato juice, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer another couple of minutes.
Serve over pasta.
Garnish with olives.

title: sharon's easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop vegetables and saute in oleo.
Boil vermicelli in chicken broth.
Add all the rest of ingredients and simmer a few minutes.

title: batterway rolls
directions: Pour water in a large bowl.
Add yeast; let stand a few minutes.
Stir until dissolved.
Add half the flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add egg; beat 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour; beat another 2 minutes.
Cover with oiled plastic wrap. Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour and 30 minutes. Grease 2 dozen small muffin tin holes.
Stir batter 20 to 25 strokes.
Spoon half full.
Let rise until batter reaches top of tins.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Brush with butter when they come out of oven.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put boiling water and oats in large mixing bowl.
Stir thoroughly and let stand 1 hour.
Add molasses, salt and butter. Put warm water and yeast into small bowl.
When yeast is dissolved, add to the oatmeal mixture.
Stir in flour.
Beat thoroughly and let rise until double in bulk.
Add enough more flour to make the dough just firm enough to knead.
Shape into 2 loaves and put in greased pans.
Let rise until almost double. Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Toss and brown sausage; drain on paper towel.
Pour off grease.
Boil for 7 minutes the soup, rice and water.
Put all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mazell's country buttercream ribbon chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 egg and 1/4 cup sugar in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed of an electric mixer until smooth. Gradually add 3 tablespoons milk and next 3 ingredients, beating well.
Set aside.

title: moussaka
directions: Brush both sides of eggplant slices with the oil. In a large skillet, brown eggplant slices over medium heat about 2 minutes per side. Drain; set aside.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: I use the stems of the cauliflower and broccoli that was leftover from the broccoli and cauliflower salad to make the soup. Boil until tender; mash and remove any stems that are stringy. Proceed with your favorite cream soup recipe.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken. Rinse chicken and pat dry.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together the bread crumbs, herb and pepper.
Add the melted margarine and toss to coat.
Sprinkle the skinned side of each chicken piece with the crumb mixture, pressing onto the chicken to coat.
Arrange chicken pieces, coating side up, in a 12 x 17 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Do not turn.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour cabbage slaw
directions: Mix together vinegar and sugar.
Heat until sugar dissolves; set aside to cool.
Shred together in food processor the cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Add celery seed, mustard seed and salt to cabbage mixture and add black pepper to taste.
When vinegar mixture is cooled, pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Chill in a closed container.
This will keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Brush chicken with Miracle Whip Light.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish/pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry-raspberry-pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart pitcher or punch bowl. Serve over ice.
Makes 11 cups.

title: weesie's coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat.
Add melted butter, then milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into an unbaked pastry shell and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Melt butter with sour cream. Add seasoning salt. Pour over cooked potatoes. Pour into baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water. Wait 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add together.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise until dough is double in bulk.
Make into rolls.
Let rise again until double in bulk. Bake.

title: hildy's roasted peppers
directions: Roast peppers and tomatoes until black in a 450° oven.
Keep in foil to keep warm while peeling.
Slice and seed.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Coat with olive oil.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: no calorie soup
directions: Cut up and place in a large pot, with enough water to see in. Let simmer until done.
Eat until you can't eat any more.

title: chicken balls
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, cream cheese, garlic salt, curry powder and lemon juice.
Add chicken and mix well.
Shape into ball or log.
Roll in chopped cashews and serve with crackers.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: molasses applesauce cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and molasses. Beat in egg. Add sifted dry ingredients and applesauce at one time.
Stir in nuts. Drop on lightly greased sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil the zucchini and onion in a little water for about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots.
Melt butter or margarine and mix with stuffing cubes.
Place half the stuffing mix in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix zucchini and onion with soup, sour cream and carrot mixture.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick spanish beef rice
directions: Add beef, onion, green pepper and rice in skillet.
Stir until meat is brown.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
One-half cup grated cheese may be added before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars, then add eggs and oil. Now mix in remaining ingredients. Chill dough overnight.
Make into small balls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with sugared fork.
Bake at 325° about 10 minutes or until edges lightly brown.

title: pecan pies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 20 minutes in a well buttered pan or muffin tin.

title: homemade orange ice cream
directions: Freeze according to freezer directions.
Also good with crushed pineapple added.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine or butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Dip each tortilla into tomato mixture to soften.
Place 1 piece of chicken and about 2 tablespoons shredded cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1-inch baking dish.

title: artichoke dip or spread
directions: Chop artichokes very fine.
Add cheese and mayonnaise and mix well.
Microwave on High in small serving dish until hot, about 4 minutes.
Stir twice while heating.
Serve warm with crackers or on raw vegetables.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into a greased and heated 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham what am
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar. Simmer about 15 minutes at low heat. Add Blue cheese. Remove from heat at once. Stir to mix and dissolve cheese. Spread on top of ham slice that has been fried just enough to heat thoroughly.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake according to box directions.
Makes two layers.
Cool and split to make 4 layers.

title: squash casserole 2
directions: Put well drained, hot squash in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, margarine, mayonnaise, sugar, half of cheese and half of cracker crumbs.
Season with cayenne pepper, salt, pepper and herbs (oregano is especially good in this dish).
Mix all ingredients well.
Put into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with remaining cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Crookneck squash or a mixture of crookneck and zucchini may be used.

title: chinatown red-cooked pork treasures
directions: In a 1-gallon self-sealing plastic bag, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Seal bag and marinate in the refrigerate 8 to 12 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. Remove pork cubes from marinade, discarding marinade.
Pat pork dry with paper towel.
Place cubes in a single layer not touching in a shallow baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until pork is just tender and lightly browned.
Remove to serving platter or chafing dish and serve hot as an appetizer.
Makes 16 servings.

title: quick krispie balls
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Turn off heat and add peanut butter and chips; stir until melted.
Mix with Rice Krispies. Pour real quick into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice.
Cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in soup, sour cream, wine and curry powder.
Stir in chicken and wild rice.
Turn into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, margarine and powdered sugar in a small bowl.
Press evenly with hands in bottom and about 5/8-inch up sides of an ungreased square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Beat remaining ingredients in a medium bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Pour over base and bake until no indentation remains when touched lightly in the center, about 25 minutes.
Let stand until cool; then cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: crepes a la alexa zoe
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor and process until smooth.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Lightly wipe a 7-inch skillet with vegetable oil and heat over medium/high heat. Add 2 tablespoons of batter.
Quickly tilt the pan back and forth to spread batter evenly over skillet.
Cook until lightly browned, then turn and cook other side until brown.
Repeat with remaining batter, stacking crepes between sheets of wax paper to prevent sticking.
Serve hot with maple syrup and ice cream (add sliced bananas if you like).

title: cheese cake -diet
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin log roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold in pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. On top, sprinkle nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Don't let cool.
Turn out on dish towel lightly sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Turn nut side onto towel.
Leave until cool.
Unroll flat.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken
and
debone;
cook ground beef and drain. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Saute onions in butter. Combine all
ingredients
in a large container and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. May be frozen.

title: zucchini bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, sugar substitute, vanilla, pineapple and zucchini.
Sift flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° in well-greased loaf pans for 40 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
May be frozen.

title: shrimp salad with grapes
directions: Bring 4-quarts water to boil.
Add salt and bay leaves.
Add shrimp, cook 1 minute.
Pour into colander.
Cool.

title: easy drop candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening together for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes (or until melted).
Stir in your choice of fillers.
(I mix 3/4 cup
nuts and 3/4 cup marshmallows for Rocky Road type candy.)
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: onion patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop teaspoonful in hot oil. Pat out flat.
Can be kept in oven 1 hour on low heat while frying all of them.

title: chocolate coconut (bourbon) balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well (takes awhile).
Mold into small balls.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over low heat in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture with a toothpick.
Let cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to liquid ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 medium loaves.

title: bacon and vegetable bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter and cheese into small bowl. Roll each biscuit piece into mixture. Arrange 1/3 of the biscuits in a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Put a layer of bacon, green pepper and onion.
Repeat, ending up with a layer of biscuits on the top.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Invert onto a serving plate. Garnish with strips of green peppers.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Crumble corned beef.
Add horseradish and mayonnaise, mixing very well.
Serve with crackers as a spread.

title: coconut-pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat well at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after adding each.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternating with milk; begin and end with flour.
Mix after adding each.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Spread one layer with half of pineapple filling.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup coconut over filling. Repeat with the next layer.
Spread frosting on top and sides of cake and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: sauteed zucchini(lo-fat)
directions: In nonstick skillet heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Add zucchini and saute until just tender and slightly browned (5 to 8 minutes). Combine remaining ingredients and add to zucchini. Remove from heat. Toss gently and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and peanut butter and beat well.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in raisins or chocolate chips.

title: crumb cake
directions: Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mexi-corn lasagna
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large skillet.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic salt; mix well.

title: black-eyed peas headliner broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together all other ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Do not drain broccoli.
Pour batter over margarine or butter.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as usual in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat to boiling 1 cup Pet milk and sugar.
Add marshmallows; when melted, add coconut.
Pour over hot cake.
Melt 1/2 cup Pet milk with butter and chocolate chips.
Spread on top of coconut.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: herb-baked fish and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine hot bouillon, uncooked rice and seasonings.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with broccoli, 1/2 can onions and the cheese. Place fish fillets diagonally down center of dish.
Sprinkle fish with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes until fish flakes.
Stir rice.
Top fish with Cheddar cheese and remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, water and salt together.
Pour over beans, celery and onion.
Let stand 24 hours. If you so desire, you may add mango and green pepper.

title: pork chops and potato combo
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook pork chops in shortening until brown; sprinkle with salt.
Heat water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan. Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake until pork chops are done, 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, then refrigerate for 1 hour. Melt together wax and Hershey bars.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mix, then in ice water.

title: baked mochi
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except potato starch.
Add water and coconut milk gradually until well mixed.
Add vanilla and coloring and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Do not underbake.
In fact, overbake. Cool completely.
Cut into smaller pieces and roll in potato starch.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 the ingredients, then repeat and layer other half. Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and brown cheese.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in Corning dish (1 1/2-quart casserole).
Place in microwave and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Return to microwave and cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet; let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container. Makes about 1 pound.

title: granny hazel's spaghetti rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and garlic powder.
Mix in 2 cups flour.
Soften yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water with the 1 teaspoon sugar added.
Mix this with the dough and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Let the dough rise while you butter muffin pans.
Stir dough well and drop by tablespoon into cornmeal.
Roll to cover and place in muffin pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: jubilee layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Continue to cream until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans in 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken into bite size pieces and mix with all other ingredients.
Put into a greased, flat casserole or baking pan and top with 2 cups crushed Fritos or potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Line dish with tortillas broken in fourths.
Spread layer of chicken over.
Pour 1 can of soup, cheese and 1/2 can of tomato peppers, then alternate layers, again topping with cheese.
Cook 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Beat together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and oil. Beat 2 minutes.
