Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin). Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in a skillet.
Drain off the fat.
In a mixing bowl, combine sauce, soup and milk. Stir in the meat.
Break the tortillas into small pieces.
Put some meat in the casserole dish to cover the bottom.
Alternate meat, tortillas and cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lentil spinach soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large soup pot or crock-pot. Cook on low for 6 hours.
If using a crock-pot, set crock-pot to high and cook 6 hours.
Add ground pepper to taste.
Can also add two chopped Italian sausages to ingredients for different flavor before cooking.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger meat, pepper and onions.
Add tomato sauce. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer pepperoni, ham, mushrooms, etc.
Then put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Mix together eggs, milk, flour and oil.
Pour over the cheese. Sprinkle more cheese on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs well.
Add flour, milk and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese, cooked spinach (well drained) and onion.
Spoon into baking dish. Level off.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash rolls
directions: Put milk, oleo, salt and sugar in saucepan until oleo melts. Dissolve yeast in warm water in another bowl.
Add squash to saucepan mixture.
Stir in 2 cups of flour at a time.
Place 2 balls in each muffin pan hole.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lite eclair dessert
directions: Prepare 12 hours in advance.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray (Pam).
Line bottom of pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding, milk, Cool Whip and yogurt with mixer at medium speed until blended.
Pour over graham crackers.
Place whole graham crackers on top, side by side.
In microwave, heat frosting until soupy (about 1 minute) and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.

title: chicken caruso and rice
directions: Season chicken with garlic salt and pepper.
Saute in butter about 2 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and Italian seasoning; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery; continue cooking until celery is tender-crisp.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch milk chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs, mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Reserve 1 cup chocolate chips for frosting.
Stir in remaining chips and nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: butterscotch chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat the sugar, brown sugar, margarine and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Blend well. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Stir in butterscotch chips.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with fork dipped in flour or sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with 1 cup of cheese.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle other cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap about 1 teaspoon of mixture around each olive, covering it completely.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: non-bake cookies
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar and 1 cup syrup 1 minute.
Add a few chocolate chips.
Take off burner.
Add 1 cup peanut butter and 2 1/2 to 3 cups crushed Post Toasties.
Drop on wax paper.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix onion, chestnuts, cheese, vegetables and mayonnaise together.
Place in baking dish; sprinkle Ritz crackers on top and dab with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook up lasagna like directions advise.
Cook up hamburg. Drain grease off.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Continue to simmer for 1 hour.
When done, use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread a little sauce in bottom of pan.
Lay down a row of noodles, then sauce, then cheese (both kinds) then drop cottage cheese by teaspoons.
Then do it all again until pan is full.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in 1-inch cubes.
Add onions; cook in a little water until tender (approximately 20 minutes).
Drain; add soup and sour cream.
Set aside.

title: wright's savory barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Use with chicken, ribs or hamburgers.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the chicken, almonds, chestnuts, pimentos and celery. Then blend mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine the chicken mixture with the blended ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: easy tuna quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread tuna over bottom of pie shell. Sprinkle cheese and onion over tuna.
Top with sliced mushrooms. Beat together eggs, milk, lemon juice and seasonings; pour over tuna mixture.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake an additional 12 to 15 minutes or until center is set.
Crab or shrimp may be substituted for tuna.
Serves 6.

title: half time meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread, milk, onion, parsley, salt and mustard.
Shape in 4 loaves.
Put in baking pan, spoon ketchup over it and bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sugar-free cocoa mix
directions: Mix well. To make cocoa, add 4 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water. Stir well.

title: indonesian pork chops(or chicken)
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
In hot skillet, brown meat on both sides in oil.
Drain peach halves and set aside.
Combine peach liquid and all other ingredients, except pepper and peaches. Pour mixture over browned meat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cut peppers into diamond shapes.
Add peppers and peaches when meat is done.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve over fluffy rice and French bread.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine in bowl the pineapple, pistachio pudding and cottage cheese; mix well.
Add pecans and Cool Whip; stir well.
Pour in salad bowl and refrigerate 1 hour minimum; overnight for best results.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: apple-nut thing
directions: Sift flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Cream eggs and brown sugar.
Add
vanilla, nuts and apples.
Add dry mixture. Pour into 2
(10-inch)
pie tins (buttered).	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool
in
pans.
Serve
with Cool Whip, but extra good with whipped cream and flavored with sherry.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: ma ma's peanut butter fudge
directions: Use half as much milk as sugar (or twice as much sugar as milk).
Cook to soft ball stage.
Put in hunk of butter, some vanilla, pinch of salt and a gob of peanut butter.
Stir well and put into buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: double-good fudge
directions: Coat eight (4 ounce) shallow baking dishes with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
Combine 1 package powdered sugar, chunky peanut butter and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons milk in a large microwave-safe bowl, stirring well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; stir until smooth.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread evenly into prepared dishes.
Place 1/2 cup butter in a separate microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave at High 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in 1 package powdered sugar, 1/4 cup milk and 1/2 cup cocoa.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at Medium-high (70%) power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; stir until smooth.
Spread chocolate mixture evenly over peanut butter layers; cool.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Place 4 cups of potatoes into 2 x 12 x 17-inch greased pan. Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 45 minutes.

title: onion casserole number 3
directions: Heat first four ingredients in saucepan.
Add onions and cook covered until tender (about 15 minutes).
Turn onion mixture into 1-quart casserole and pour a mixture of egg yolks, sour cream, and cheese over onions.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue baby beef ribs
directions: Wipe ribs with wet towel or with damp paper towel.
Place ribs in a single layer in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast ribs at 450° for about 20 minutes, turning once.
Prepare basting sauce.
Mix all ingredients together.
Remove ribs from oven.
Brush ribs with sauce on both sides.
Return to oven.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes longer or until ribs are tender.
Baste with remaining sauce from time to time while baking.
If ribs start to get too dark, cover with aluminum foil and reduce heat to 400° for the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except potato chips and margarine).
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips mixed with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the first ingredients. In pan,
put margarine, oil, cocoa and water. Bring to a boil. Pour over flour mixture and stir well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Mix well. Batter is thin. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Boil until soft ball can be formed in cup of cold water*.
Remove from heat.
Stir until thick.
Spoon onto buttered wax paper.

title: pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 large baking sheets.
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir until blended and yeast is dissolved.
Gradually, with wooden spoon, stir in sugar, salt and enough flour for sticky dough.

title: virginia's apple cheese dessert
directions: Fill shallow greased baking dish with apples. Sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar. Mix flour, cinnamon, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is granular. Stir in cheese. Pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs. Add the milk, oil and vinegar.
Add flour and salt. Beat until free from lumps. Add the water and mix well. Leave the batter for 30 or more minutes.
Pour a little oil into a frying pan and allow the pan to heat well.
Pour the excess oil off and fry the batter.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix oleo and
Crisco together; gradually add sugar.
When mixed, add eggs 1 at a time.
Mix baking powder and salt with flour; add to creamed mixture.
When all flour has been added, add flavorings and sour cream.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours; test with toothpick to be sure cake is done.
Let cool in pan for 20 minutes before removing cake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pick chicken from bone; cube.
Combine chicken, Veg-All and soup.
Put in pie crust and cover with remaining crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked fish in herb butter
directions: Bake fish for about 5 minutes.
Put mushrooms and green onions on top.
Melt together in saucepan the margarine, soy sauce, oregano, garlic salt and thyme.
Pour the butter mixture on top of all.
Make sure that the mushrooms are well basted, then bake for about 8 minutes more at 400° to 450°.
If the fish are very thick, add a couple of minutes to baking time before or after pouring on the sauce.

title: italian flat bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese; stir in basil, oregano, green onions and garlic. Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
On ungreased cookie sheets, press or roll out each biscuit to 4-inch circle.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of cheese mixture over each circle to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: veggie roll
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rolls, in a bowl.
Unroll crescent rolls in a rectangle.
Overlap two rectangles and pinch seams. Spoon stuffing down middle of the two rectangles.
Cut slits at 1-inch intervals along the sides of the rectangle.
Braid slits over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jiffy tater-turkey or beef casserole
directions: Press meat (uncooked) into an 8-inch square pan.
Season with salt, pepper and onion.
Pour on soup.
Sprinkle peas over soup. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Soak raisins in hot water, drain on paper towel.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy, then beat in eggs, then applesauce and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Stir into mixture.
Add raisins and nuts and mix well.
Bake in oblong pan (9 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch) at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool on rack, frost if desired.

title: blushing betty
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in an oblong 12 x 8-inch pan.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Drain mixed vegetables and cover chicken.
Mix mushroom soup with broth and pour over vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and milk to make thin batter and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients and shape into loaf.
Put in microwave dish.
Put it in the microwave oven and put wax paper over it.
Cook 8 minutes, then take it out.
Cut the meat loaf in two and put it back in the microwave oven and bake another 5 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix melted margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar, then stir in Cool Whip. Spread on crust, then pour pie filling on top; place in fridge until firm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Empty 2
cans
of
corn into baking dish.
Make a white sauce with flour, butter and milk.
Add 2 beaten eggs.
Add to corn
and mix.
Salt
as
desired,
about
teaspoon.
If desired, sprinkle a little grated cheese on top of casserole. Bake at
350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Place in dish of water to bake.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter or margarine by hand like pie dough.
Mix vanilla, sour milk, soda, salt and egg with spoon. Bake in long pan.
Take out 1 cup crumbs before you put liquid in.
Beat with spoon.
Spread crumbs on top.
You may sprinkle with cinnamon if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot corny cornbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (dry) in bowl.
Make well in middle; add next 4 ingredients (wet).
Beat liquids well; widen strokes to include dry.
Do not overmix (batter should be lumpy).
Fold in last 4 ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan or muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir boiling
water
and oatmeal together and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream
shortening
with the sugars.
Add eggs and beat in.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture. Add
oatmeal
and
beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch square pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Coconut Topping.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cook bacon slices and cut them up. Mix beans, vinegar, brown sugar and catsup in large bowl.
Add hamburger and bacon pieces.
Mix well.
Spread in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken desire
directions: Lightly grease or spray casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish and cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
Spread soup over cheese.
Mix margarine and stuffing and put on top of soup.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.

title: salad
directions: Mix this all together.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 5 ingredients for the icing.
Spread on after it has cooled.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls to cover the bottom of a 15 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on filling.
Press vegetables into filling, slightly.
Refrigerate and cut into bars. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: friendship cake
directions: Take starter juice and add 2 1/2 cups sugar and large can sliced peaches (juice too).
Stir daily for 10 days.
Then add 2 1/2 cups sugar and chunked pineapple.
Stir daily for 10 days. Add 2 1/2 cups sugar, maraschino cherries and fruit cocktail. Stir daily for 10 days.
Drain juice from fruit.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 Tbsp juice.
Combine brown sugar and butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan. Place a cherry half, cut side up, in center of each slice. Sprinkle with reserved juice and nuts.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Mix water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil. Put 1 head of dill and 1 section of garlic in each jar before cucumbers are added.
Wash and slice cucumbers long way (about 1/4 or 1/2 inch slices).
Place in jars and add boiling vinegar mixture.
Seal jars.
Yields 6 or 7 quarts.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: comfort eggnog
directions: Chill ingredients.
Blend in punch bowl by beating; dust with nutmeg.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add salt.
Pour into buttered casserole. Put frozen onion rings on meat.
Drain beans; save the liquid. Spread beans on top of this.
Mix liquid from beans with the can of chicken soup; pour over top.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cookie cake
directions: Place the sugar and flour in a mixing bowl.
Place the water, oil, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring mixture in saucepan to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour cooked mixture over flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add the eggs and buttermilk.
Add the vanilla; mix well.
Pour into floured and greased sheet pan, 1/2-inch deep.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Start topping 10 minutes before cake is done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix together the oil, sugar and eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add carrots and nuts, stirring to blend.
Bake at 325° in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix everything together and refrigerate a few hours to allow flavors to blend.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt oil and butter in pan.
Add onions.
Stir well, cover and cook, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
When onions are soft, add sugar and salt.
Increase heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook until golden brown.
Pour in broth and wine with pepper.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Slice bread in half and toast on grill on both sides.
Pile a little of cheese on each piece of toast and return to grill to melt.
Add cognac to soup, then float the toasted bread on top just before serving.

title: crunchy date chewies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg, almond extract and evaporated milk and beat well. Sift together and add flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add to the batter. Mix a little and add nuts, dates, coconut, oats and corn flakes. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool 2 minutes before removing from pan. Yield: about 3 dozen.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer in glass casserole dish in order given.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic lightly in salad oil over medium heat.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and seasonings; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package, leaving them slightly uncooked.
Drain.

title: southern banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil and sugar.
Add 2 eggs, bananas and baking soda.
Add vanilla and Bisquick.
Grease and flour loaf pan and place mixture in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Recipe can also be used for "magic muffins".

title: mother's noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness as directed on package; drain.
Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl, combine cream cheese and margarine; blend well.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese, salt, sugar and eggs.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes or until set.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: microwave beef jerky with fresh ginger
directions: Combine ginger, honey, sesame oil, soy sauce, wine, garlic and cayenne.
Add steak to marinade, tossing to coat well.
Marinate at room temperature, tossing occasionally, for 3 hours.
Remove meat from marinade and arrange half the strips, flat and close together, on a microwave bacon rack.
Cover with paper towels and cook on Medium-low 20 minutes.
Rotate strips so that drier strips are in the center. Cover with fresh paper towel and cook on Medium-low for 15 to 20 minutes until meat is dry but slightly pliable.
Remove to a large wire rack and let stand overnight. Repeat with remaining strips.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Finely chop all ingredients and combine.
If too spicy, add fewer peppers.

title: rex jelly
directions: Mix beet juice and Sure-Jell together and cook 1 minute.
Add 2 boxes raspberry jello and sugar.
Cook 6 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Yield 6 pints.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend date filling and water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with date mixture to butter mixture.
Beat 1 minute.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 prepared 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in iron skillet or baking dish.	Combine all ingredients including the melted margarine from the skillet. Mix and pour into greased skillet.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown at 450°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken breasts and save broth. Cut up chicken into bite-size pieces.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of stuffing mix that has been mixed with melted butter.
Next, layer 1/2 of chicken.
Mix 3/4 cup of broth to cream of chicken soup and pour this over 1st layer.
Next, layer remainder of chicken, then mix 3/4 cup of broth to cream of mushroom soup and pour over top, then layer remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water.
In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour. Add
broth and stir.
Cook until thick. Add remaining ingredients and cook until done. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook sliced zucchini, chopped onion, parsley and spices together (use big frying pan); really cooks down.
Drain.
Mix eggs and cheese together.
Spread crescent roll dough in pie plate. Spread yellow mustard over dough.
Mix zucchini mixture, egg and cheese mixture; put in pie crust and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel bread pudding
directions: Combine brown sugar, water and margarine; bring to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute; set aside.
Combine and mix together biscuit mix, 1/4 cup brown sugar and raisins, then add the milk.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch greased dish.
Pour on the hot syrup.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: over the rainbow cookies
directions: Allow dough to soften at room temperature.
Divide dough into four equal parts.

To first portion of dough, add 2 drops blue food coloring; to second portion, add 2 drops green coloring; to third portion, add 2 drops red coloring and to fourth portion, add 2 drops yellow coloring.
On plastic wrap or waxed paper, shape green dough into 8-inch log.
Press dough slightly to flatten one side.
Cover roll carefully with blue dough, keeping semi-circular shape.
Continue layering yellow and red doughs in same manner, gently pressing layers of dough together.
Wrap; chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: polly olson's tea cookies(polly was pastry chef at oviedo inn, oviedo, florida)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar together. Add vanilla and flour, mixing well.
Add soda and salt; mix well. Add nutmeg and eggs.
Mix on medium speed until blended.
Pour out on well floured table or board.
Divide in half.
Roll out 2 strips about 2 inches thick.
Chill for about 2 hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices and place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 375° oven until light brown.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cocoa, then add the egg, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Grease a deep 7-inch square pan and dust with flour.
Spread the dough evenly in the pan and bake in an oven at 325° until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Add butter.
Let these reach room temperature. Cream with mixer; gradually add flour, salt and pepper.
Use star plate or cookie press to shape on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 dozen.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In
saucepan
combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mash 1 cup berries. Add water to make 2 cups and stir into sugar mixture. Cook, stir and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, gelatin
and
lemon
juice;
stir
until gelatin is dissolved. Chill
until
partially
set.
Pour
1/3 mixture in pie shell. Add whole berries and cover with remaining mixture.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: beer cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add beer and mix well. Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, nuts, dates and spices. Combine beer and flour mixture and mix well.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and put on icing.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Brown onion in oleo.
Add soup and broth; mix well, then add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add chicken and salt (or season to your choice).
Cook noodles 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour chicken mixture over noodles or spaghetti and enjoy.

title: white chile
directions: Combine everything and simmer for 1-2 hours.
Top with grated jack cheese before serving.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausages, onion and celery. Drain well. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° in a covered container
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour and meal together.
In a separate bowl, beat egg; add buttermilk and oil.
Pour liquid ingredients into bowl with dry ingredients.
Stir good.
Grease pan with Pam or margarine.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cajun burgers
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into patties. Broil, fry or grill to desired doneness.
Toast buns.
Top each burger with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: doritos dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Spread on cookie sheet. Add choice of toppings.
Serve with Doritos.

title: flan
directions: Place 1/4 cup of sugar in a saucepan and melt over low heat to caramelize.
Sugar will liquify and turn light brown.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish and coat bottom.

title: crabmeat hors d'0euvres
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on split English muffins.
Freeze, then cut into quarters.
Broil (still frozen) until browned. Serve while still warm.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place raw chicken in Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with other ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered with foil.
Remove foil last 10 minutes.
Can easily
be cut in half.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: powdered sugar balls
directions: Blend together all but flour and nuts.
Slowly add flour and nuts.
Roll into small 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot (the 1/2 cup listed goes into cookie dough).

title: impossible chicken quiche
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Spread into greased deep dish pie pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour over the other mixture. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and water.
Put rice in bottom of pan and pour half soup mixture over rice.
Put in chicken pieces and pour the rest of the soup over the chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top. Cover with foil and forget it for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon (be sure to sift).
Mix well and add carrots.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: devilish chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating and ending with ice water.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with a fluffy white icing.

title: spaghetti "au gratin"
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion with butter until soft.
Add flour.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles for 1 minute.
Stir in salt, pepper and mustard.
Remove from heat and add 3/4 of the Parmesan cheese.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and pour off grease. Add onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper. Simmer until tender. Wash rice and add to mixture. Add soups and pour into baking dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, stirring occasionally.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
(Right in the pan, not in a bowl!!)
Now, with your fingers or a spoon, make three holes in the dry ingredients.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and orange peel.
Add orange juice and cook until thickened.
Add margarine.
Mix with cooked carrots. Serves about 10.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding a small amount of water to thick consistency.
Drop in deep oil; cook in temperature of 375°.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Divide popcorn into two ungreased pans. Place butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook until bubbly and then cook 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir.
Bake 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: italian corn and rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the salsa, tomato juice, brown rice, onion, seasonings and 2 cups of water.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: choco-crumble bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter.
Mix and pat in pan.
Bake "crust" at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over baked crust.
Refrigerate until "set."
Cut into bars to serve.

title: cranberry-brandy punch
directions: To serve warm, combine all ingredients in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain and mix with other ingredients, except cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted or browned.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: kraut relish
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.
Very good.

title: polish rafts
directions: Fry together meats, drain off grease.
Add in cheese and melt in with meat.
Put on party rye and bake for about 20 minutes. Very Good, Very Easy.

title: mustard steak
directions: Lay steaks out.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread mustard over meat.
Top with chopped onion and press onion into meat with hand.
Flour lightly and place in hot skillet with about 1/4 cup oil.
Cook on medium heat until done.
Turn once and brown other side.
Serve on hot platter, onion side up.
Cook side with onion first.

title: oven-fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings.
Spray a large baking sheet with nonstick coating.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together bread crumbs, melted margarine, salt and if desired, ground red pepper.
Spread mixture on a sheet of waxed paper. Using a fork, dip onion rings into egg whites, then bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in a single layer on prepared baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until onions are tender and coating is crisp and golden.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil vegetables in broth until tender. Cut bread into chunks. Crumble cornbread. Mix all ingredients together. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cherry delight
directions: Spread on graham cracker
crust.
Spread
can cherry pie filling on top of this.
Top with chopped nuts (optional). Refrigerate.

title: corn bread(60 muffins)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into hot greased 13 x 9 pan or muffin pans. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Will make about 60 muffins.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add butter, brown sugar, milk, salt and orange rind.
With a tablespoon, scoop up about 1/4 cup of mixture and shape around a marshmallow, using more potato, if needed, to form a ball.
Roll each ball in cornflakes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and cake mix.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add oil, water and strawberries (save 1/4 or more berries for icing on cake).
Cook layers in 3-inch cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cakes completely before icing.

title: diabetic reese's cups
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with wax paper.
Butter paper slightly. Melt chocolate in a double boiler until melted.
Pour 1/2 of chocolate into pan to make a thin layer.
Let cool until hard. Mix graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter (amount of each depends on your desires).
Spread evenly over hardened chocolate. Pour remaining chocolate over peanut butter mixture.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all but cinnamon together.
Put cinnamon on top.
Serve with different fruit slices or strawberries.

title: lavender cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and lavender and mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to lavender mixture until well blended.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Remove from oven when done and poke holes all over it.
Pour the milk and cream of coconut over and let soak in.
When cool spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients except for muffins.
Spread on muffin halves (12 pieces).
Broil until hot.
Slice each muffin half into quarters.

title: scallopini chicken
directions: Season flour with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Dredge breasts in flour mixture, then in eggs, then bread crumbs and cheese, which have been combined.
Melt butter in a skillet and brown breasts on both sides.
Continue cooking for about 5 minutes or until done. Yield: 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, milk and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter and dry ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Press with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Bring all ingredients, using as many hot peppers as desired, to a boil.
Reduce heat, cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until desired thickness.
Stir occasionally.
Pour in 5 pint jars and seal.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on griddle until golden brown.

title: big boy strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and gelatin; add water and lemon juice. Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in gently into 1 quart strawberries. Pour in 9-inch baked shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.

title: flat bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add buttermilk gradually; mix in salt and whole wheat flour.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together, add all at one time.
Mix well.
Roll out on a pastry cloth until almost paper thin.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until brown and crisp.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Soak bread in margarine. Add grated cheese, milk, pepper, salt, mustard and egg yolks. Mix together. Fold in egg whites into mixture. Pour into buttered dish. Chill 12 to 24 hours. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients into mayonnaise.
Mix in crab meat. Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Use crackers for dipping.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients thoroughly.
Press in loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and drain off excess fat.

title: caramel corn(cracker jacks)
directions: Bring all ingredients, except popcorn and soda, to a boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soda quickly.
Pour over popcorn and peanuts; stir well.
Place in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Stir while cooling.
Reduce salt to 1/2 teaspoon if no peanuts or salted peanuts are added.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Sift together flour and cocoa.
Mix flour and cocoa mixture with sugar.
Add milk and well beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; beat in butter or margarine; add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Using remaining egg whites, make meringue and spread on top of pie.
Let brown.

title: maraschino cherry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir well and add shortening, cherry juice, cherries and milk.
Beat for two minutes.
Add egg whites; beat 2 minutes.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour mixture into 2 round waxed layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: many ways meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs; pour off drippings. Stir in soup, water and parsley.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Can serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: ranch beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion.
Drain fat.
Use all juices from beans except yellow bean juice.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 4-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: paul henry's cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini like French fries.
In frying pan, fry zucchini with onions in butter.
Place lid on pan and continue cooking until onions are tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Put zucchini mixture into a large casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Add the mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, cheddar cheese, stuffing and sauce; mix well.
Sprinkle some cheese on top and back at 375 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Toss to mix.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa and cola; bring to boil.
Pour over mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, vanilla and marshmallows; mix well.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: glaze baked ham
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place ham, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast about 15 to 18 minutes per pound or until a meat thermometer registers 140° about 4 to 4 3/4 hours. While ham is roasting, mix orange marmalade, corn syrup and dry mustard together.
Remove ham from oven and cut off rind. Increase oven temperature to 375°.
Score ham with a sharp knife, making diagonal cuts 1/8-inch deep and about 3/4-inch apart in one direction and then in a crosswise direction.
Stud ham with cloves and brush with some of the glaze.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, basting frequently with more glaze until glaze is golden brown.
Remove the ham to a warm serving platter.
Serves 16 generously.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Mix Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla with mixer until blended.
Grease and flour pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Pour batter in pan (cake).
Top with Ricotta mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool; top with pie filling.

title: beef stew
directions: In skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add beef; brown on all sides.
Add next 4 ingredients and 4 cups of the water. Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and onions.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until tender.
Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Stir into beef mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potatoes parmesan
directions: Cut peeled raw potatoes into bite sized pieces.
Melt the margarine on a lipped cookie sheet.
Combine in a bowl the cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip the pieces in the melted margarine. Coat with the cheese and flour mixture.
Place coated pieces on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix well. Pat into deep 9-inch pan. Place in refrigerator 1 hour before filling.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles in water until done. While cooking, mix together eggs, milk and margarine in a bowl. Add salt and pepper. When noodles are ready, put into a sheet cake pan or something similar and pour mixture of eggs, milk and margarine over the top. Bake in oven at 350° until completely cooked.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and seasonings.

title: dried tea mix lemon allspice
directions: Dry peel in 200° oven.
Mix ingredients and store in airtight jar.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, butter, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Press half of mixture into a greased baking pan.
If desired, reserve half of mixture for topping.
Cover with rhubarb.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream, if desired.
Yield: 9 to 12 servings.

title: doris' dishpan cookies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil, oleo and vanilla thoroughly.
Add sifted flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well with creamed mixture.
Add corn flakes, oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Blend well. Drop by teaspoon or roll into balls and press with fork.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 15 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, raisins and nuts. Mix thoroughly.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in flour until batter is very stiff.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crawfish imperial
directions: In large skillet, saute onions, bell peppers, garlic and celery until tender in about 1/2 cup of butter flavored Crisco. Add about 1/4 cup flour to thicken.
Add parsley flakes, tomatoes, tomato sauce and crawfish.
Lower heat and cook, covered, for 30 minutes to an hour.
When ready to serve, stir in Cheez Whiz. Serve over rice.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: In 2-quart ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients; mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Cut up spinach in a bowl.
Combine above ingredients.
Pour over spinach.
You can add bacon and boiled eggs, if desired.

title: pork tenderloin stuffed with sausage
directions: Trim all fat from the loin.
Cut a slit down the middle of the loin and season to taste.
Stuf loin with sausage and secure with toothpicks.
Add butter to a 12-inch skillet and heat until butter foams. Brown loin in butter approximately 5 minutes on each side. Remove loin to a baking dish.
To the remaining butter, add onions and water.
Reduce on medium heat about 8 minutes.
Pour sauce over loin and cover with foil.
Place in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until loin is tender.
Bake uncovered for last 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken without salt.
Take meat off bones.
Melt margarine; stir into dressing mix.
Grease large dish and put a layer of dressing crumbs and a layer of chicken, layer of chicken soup mixed with 1 can of chicken broth.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Cool.
Make holes in top of cake and pour butterscotch topping over cake (reserve 1/8 of jar to drizzle over icing).
Ice cake with Cool Whip.
Crumble Butterfingers and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Drizzle remaining butterscotch topping over this.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: italian tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes about 1-inch thick.
Dice onions.
Slice green and yellow peppers.
Mix with Italian dressing.

title: cheesy gravy
directions: In saucepan combine all ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Serve over chicken or mashed potatoes. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Measure dry ingredients into a bowl, then sift.
Blend dry ingredients with the creamed mixture (spoon works best; batter is very thick at this point).
Add vanilla and sour cream, mixing until thoroughly blended.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan, spreading evenly.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 325°, until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan and tester comes out of the center clean.
Let cake stand in pan for 10 minutes before inverting pan on a rack to remove cake.
Cut into thin slices.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Line casserole pan with sliced potatoes.
Spread meat over potatoes, then other ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: maple chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Cut off chicken wing tips and snip the skin between the joints. Place in a disposable large baking pan. Add the maple syrup, soy sauce, teriyaki sauce, garlic, garlic powder, onion powder, and pepper, toss to coat.

title: toasted pecan pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, combine butter, coconut, flour, pecans and sugar. Spread into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, powder and salt.
Add milk, salad oil, water and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except grated cheese).
Bake in greased casserole dish 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: mediterranean pilaf
directions: Bring broth and water to a boil in a saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 19 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Yields 4 cups.
Serving size is 1/2 cup.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium heat.
Drain fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer 15-20 minutes.
Spoon into a large kettle or roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
about 25 servings.

title: after christmas salad
directions: Toss meat and macaroni together until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco until soft, then add eggs and sugar; mix well. Add cake flour and milk; mix until well blended, then add the vanilla, orange and butter flavorings. Make sure everything is mixed well together. Pour batter into a Bundt cake pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine and pack into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer the remaining in order given: coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and chopped pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over layers and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tamale corn
directions: Mix chilies and grated cheese.
Mix eggs, creamed corn, cornmeal, garlic, baking powder and oil.
Place all of corn mixture in baking dish, then layer with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered potato salad
directions: In large glass bowl, layer a third of the cabbage and a third of the potatoes.
Next, layer a third of the onion rings, pepper rings and egg slices.
Cover completely with mayonnaise.
Repeat layers twice, always ending with egg and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: *Note:
Wear gloves (rubber) when working with jalapeno peppers!

title: tuna vegetable souffle
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Prepare 4 servings mashed potatoes (omit butter).
Fold in mayonnaise.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour into greased 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serve at once.

title: ho-bo steaks
directions: Make ground beef into round patties.
Place on foil-lined sheet.
Top each patty with salt, pepper and one slice of onion. Place potatoes and carrots on and around.
Cover cookie sheet with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: * elephant stew *
directions: Cut elephant into 1-inch cubes, frequently adding pinches of salt and pepper (this should take approximately 72 days).
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
If more than 3,800 people are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: weight watchers stir-fried cabbage
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine over high until bubbly and hot.

Add celery and cook, stirring quickly and frequently, for 1 minute. Add cabbage, bell pepper and onion; continue to stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp, 2 to 3 minutes. Add soy sauce and pepper.
Stir well. Cook for 1 minute longer.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving provides 1 3/4 vegetable exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.
Per serving contains 40 calories, 1 g protein, 2 g fat, 5 g carbohydrate, 33 mg calcium, 508 mg sodium and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: barbecue
directions: Put some meat in barbecue sauce and put some corn and fire on it.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, pepper and onions.
Heat remaining ingredients and bring to full boil over high heat, stirring.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let cool.
Cover and store in refrigerator. Will keep for days.

title: icebox pie
directions: You can use orange juice and orange jello to make an orange pie.

title: old-fashioned biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits into bowl.
Add cocoa and milk.
Let soak about 30 minutes or until biscuits are soft.
Add sugar and eggs. Mix thoroughly.

title: diet jello salad
directions: Pour the pineapple over any flavor Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is melted.
Add cottage cheese.
Stir until blended, then blend in the whipped topping.
Stir until completely mixed.
Pour into any container with a lid and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Keeps good.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in the boiling water.
Add the cold water, pineapple juice, lemon juice and almond extract.
Place punch into a plastic gallon ice cream bucket and freeze.
Thaw 4 to 6 hours and place into punch bowl.
Add the 7-Up and serve. Makes 1 1/2 gallons of delicious punch.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and peanut butter together.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla, Karo and soda. Stir in oatmeal and candies last. Bake at 375°.
Make the cookies large. Serves 150.

title: buttermilk bread
directions: Mix in a bowl dates, sugar, butter and boiling water.
Stir until the butter melts.
Cool.
Stir in egg, baking soda, flour, salt and chopped nuts.
Put in a buttered loaf pan, 9 x 5-inches. Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon croquets
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Take large amounts of mixture and form cakes.
Place in hot oil and fry until brown.

title: russian tea ball cookies
directions: Shape in balls,
after
baking
roll
in powdered sugar while hot, then when cold.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Rabbits to fry must be young or parboiled.
Cut into joints; soak for an hour in salt and water.
Dip in beaten egg, then in powdered cracker and fry brown in sweet lard or butter.
Serve with onion sauce; garnish with sliced lemon.

title: asparagus tomato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs with next 4 ingredients. Stir in cheese.
Chop 4 asparagus spears into 1-inch lengths and lay them in bottom of pie shell.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and quickly arrange tomato and the other 6 asparagus spears on top.
Bake another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: country ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown ribs on both sides in large skillet.
Spread kraut over the ribs.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the sauerkraut.
Pour water slowly over all.
Put lid on and cook over low to medium heat for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Spoon the brown juices over the kraut and serve.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour and Rice Krispies. Mixture will be dry and will have to be kneaded like biscuit dough.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon cookies on cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: frozen punch(beverage)
directions: Mix and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
Will be a slush type punch.

title: southern fried okra
directions: Wash and cut okra into 1/2-inch slices, cutting across as you cut through the cut pieces, into a large mixing bowl.
The cut okra will have a slimy feeling to it.
For about every 3 cups of cut okra you'll want to add 1 egg; stir well.
Okra should be well coated with egg.

title: 3-step white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Stir in 1/3 C. of the white chocolate.

title: grandmother's oatmeal pie(1930)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ramen noodle vegetable salad
directions: In a bowl, break up uncooked Ramen noodles.
Do not use the seasoning packet.
In a saucepan, cook vegetables until tender. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Blend into Ramen noodles.
Pour over Italian dressing and stir.
Refrigerate for at least 5 hours before serving.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and melt 1 stick of margarine; pour over topping.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet  and sour sauce for wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornstarch and bring to a boil. Mix the cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water, then add to mixture for thickening.
Serve over cooked chicken wings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a heavy skillet, stirring constantly for 3 minutes on medium heat.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Cool and form into small balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: best bean soup(serves 8)
directions: Place beans in a large pot with water to cover.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 hour.
Drain and discard water.
Add 8 cups of water and the rest of ingredients, then simmer for 2 hours over very low heat.

title: hamburger mazetti
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook beef, onion, celery, green peppers, salt and pepper.
Spoon off fat or drain on paper towels. Place noodles in casserole dish; toss with butter.
Stir in meat mixture with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: just for kids: kassie's kandi-bar surprise
directions: Place a 4-square portion of milk chocolate bar on 1 graham cracker.
Place 2 marshmallows on long fork.
Roast slowly over open fire or coals.
Let brown gradually so the center will melt. With a spoon, move the toasted marshmallows off the fork onto the chocolate.
Top with another graham cracker.
Squeeze together.

title: apricot brandy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze until ready to serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken with water to cover in pot; add granules. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook until done.
Let cool in broth, then
remove skin and bones and fat.
Pull chicken into pieces of desired size.

title: beef vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Add pepper, corn, beans and seasoning.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Add tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy "veggie" sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and warm over low heat, stirring often.
Serve over vegetables and baked potatoes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: choco butternut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat margarine and brown sugar.
Add vanilla; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine cereal and flour.
Add cereal mixture to margarine mixture.
Add pecans and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Let cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove to cool on wire racks.
If desired, roll in powdered sugar while still warm and again when cool.
Makes 3 dozen.
Enjoy.

title: "mama springer's" homemade bread
directions: In large bowl, sift 6 cups of flour.
Add salt.
Mix with wire beater.
In small bowl, place margarine and 3 cups flour.
Mix together with wire food cutter.
Save water from potatoes you cook to eat.
Small pieces of potatoes left in water is okay.
Heat potato water and add sugar.
Cool to 100°.
At 100° add yeast.
Mix well with wire beater.
Add potato water with sugar and yeast to large bowl with 6 cups of flour.
Mix well, then add contents of small bowl.
Mix together well.
(You will need to add more sifted flour now and then.)
Work well with hands until it molds together.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs.
Add chocolate chips and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: welcome home frances potluck carrots
directions: Using coarsest disk in food processor, chunk carrots.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook in microwave on High 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir carrots, cooking liquid and all, with the mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbs and dot with margarine. Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb and strawberry pie
directions: Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with butter.
Put topping on it.
Put Reynolds Wrap around pie crust and cook at 375° for 25 minutes.
Take off wrap and bake another 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Mix egg white and water.
Whip until frothy.
Add cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Then add nuts or pecans.
Spread on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Toss every 15 minutes.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Add a jar of cooked prunes, with the pits removed, to a 6 ounce package of Jell-O dissolved in the proper amount of water (according to directions on Jell-O box).
Let it set while chilling.
Beat heavy cream (1/2 pint) and sweeten to taste.
Beat Jell-O mixture and cream together and serve or keep chilled until serving time.

title: cheese salsa dip
directions: Mix salsa and eggs together.
Combine cheeses.
Put half of cheese mixture in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares and serve with Town House crackers.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Sift sugar, milk and cocoa.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Blend well.
Add water until you can form in ball.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins, in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan or 3-quart microwave casserole dish.
Mix well.
Bake in a conventional oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes. Stir in raisins.
Cool thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container in cool, dry place.

title: donuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk, then flour, sifted with salt, baking powder and spices.
Roll out on floured surface 3/8-inches; cut with doughnut cutter.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Fry in deep hot Crisco (375°); drain on paper towels.
Makes 3 dozen.
Can ice if desired.

title: noodle lasagna
directions: Pour spaghetti sauce and water into large pot.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in noodles; cover and cook 7 minutes, stirring occasionally until noodles are barely tender.
Blend ricotta cheese with seasonings and egg.
In greased 9 inch square pan, alternate layers of noodles/sauce with ricotta cheese and mozzarella cheese ending with noodles in sauce for top layer. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes and let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Add to gelatin mixture; mix well.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple, cherries and almonds.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise and shredded cheese, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter in mixer.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk and add to first mixture.	Add bananas, nuts, vanilla and salt in flour.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour then cover it with foil and bake another 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before shaking pan gently to loosen loaf from pan edges.
Leave in pan another 10 to 15 minutes before removing and cooling on a wire rack.

title: fried donuts
directions: Take biscuits and flatten each one.
Cut biscuits into fours and roll into a ball.
Heat oil in frying pan under light fire. Place biscuits in oil, cook until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: orange candy slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add soda to the other half cup buttermilk.
Add to mixture.
Combine dry ingredients. Add orange slices, halved.
Add dates and nuts.
Blend well.
Line tube pan with well-greased brown paper.
Bake slowly at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: waffles
directions: Mix all together in bowl.

title: chicken with dill sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Halve cutlets and pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Dredge in flour seasoned with 1 tablespoon dill weed and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat a 10-inch skillet and add 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute chicken until golden on both sides. Remove chicken to an ovenproof pan and cover with foil.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables, corn and beans.
Add soup, sour cream, onion, pepper and celery.
Mix these ingredients in a baking dish. Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Mix margarine and crackers together and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat meal in a skillet
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper; brown in a heavy skillet, stirring frequently.
Cover with corn and onions.
Sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Add tomatoes and do not stir.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: thumb cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add flour and vanilla; beat well. Shape dough in balls size of a marble. Place on lightly greased baking sheet and make a hole in the middle with thumb.
Fill hole with preserves or jelly. Pull dough up around the filling.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove promptly and cool on wire rack.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix thawed lemonade, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill until firm.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Simmer chicken in water to cover until tender. Bake pork until done at 325°. Shred meat with fingers into smallest possible pieces, discarding skin, fat and bones. Combine in large heavy pot with vegetables and reserved chicken broth.
Simmer 6 to 8 hours until thickened. As stew thickens, season to taste with all other ingredients. The secret is in long slow simmering.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Mix Bisquick, cornmeal and 1/2 cup water until dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Put in pan with floured hands, forming 1/2-inch rim. Bake 10 minutes.
Cook beef until brown; drain.
Stir in chilies, taco mix and 3/4 water.
Heat to boiling.
Stir frequently; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered, stirring frequently until thick, 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread beans over baked crust, top with beef mix and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Top with lettuce, onion and tomatoes.

title: tangy lemon frosting
directions: Mix together the shortening, salt, 1 cup sugar and lemon peel. (Eight to 10 drops of yellow food coloring can be added if desired.)
Add lemon juice, water and remaining sugar and mix until smooth and creamy.

title: indian curried beans
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick frying pan.
Add garlic, ginger and chopped onion and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add diced tomatoes and cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add curry powder and prepared beans.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook on medium heat for 10 more minutes.
Garnish with Garam Masala and finely chopped cilantro.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Place chicken into bowl.
Pour buttermilk over; marinate 1 hour.
In another bowl, mix flour, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Remove the chicken from buttermilk; roll chicken pieces in seasoning mixture.
Reserve the buttermilk and pour into buttered casserole.
Heat shortening and margarine in heavy skillet; fry chicken just until brown.
Remove, scrape up brownings, and add chicken broth.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Place chicken on top of buttermilk in casserole.
Pour all your scraped up brownings over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rich coconut cream pie by wanda smith
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan. Stir in egg yolks. Turn heat on medium and slowly stir in milk. Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. When mixture thickens, remove from heat and add butter, coconut and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Chill for 2 hours. Add meringue or whipped topping and sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Tie all spices except nutmeg in a cheesecloth bag.
Heat cider and brown sugar together; add spice bag and let simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove bag and serve with dash of nutmeg in each mug. Makes 7 cups.

title: no-cook fruit cake
directions: Combine
first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; let stand for
a few
minutes.
Add
remaining
ingredients, stir well. Pour batter
into a greased 10-inch tube pan, packing mixture with hands,
a small amount at a time.
Store in refrigerator until serving time.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Take center of mushroom and cut up sausage and mix.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Stuff mushroom with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chopped steaks and gravy
directions: Spray baking dish with vegetable spray.
Mix thoroughly in small bowl flour and Tony Chachere's seasoning.
In large skillet, heat enough oil to barely cover bottom.
Flour one steak at a time by lightly shaking side to side.
Turn steak, flour other side. Shake off excess.
Brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish. Put onion soup mix on top.
Cover with water.
Cover with foil tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender; skin and slice.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Add sliced beets.
Return to a boil; cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and both soups into a baking dish, cover with onion rings, then cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions, celery and peppers until soft.
Press through a food mill or sieve.
Cook on high until it starts to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low until thick. Stir frequently.
Do not let it stick to the bottom of the pot. When sauce is as thick as you like, remove the bay leaf and let it cool.
When cooled enough, put in refrigerator for 2 days.
It is now ready to use.
Just add meat or freeze some.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: meat loaf with glazed onions
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Work together, beef, pork, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, onions, catsup, egg, milk and crumbs.
Shape into a loaf; place in a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange onions in a 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt; cover onions.
Bake meat loaf and onions 1 hour.
Remove both from oven. Sprinkle onions with sugar.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Arrange meat and onions on warm serving platter.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown in hot fat the pork and onion.
Add celery, green pepper, rice, stock, salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Uncover last 10 minutes.
Serve hot in shallow bowls. Serves 6.

title: zesty snack mix
directions: In large bowl, combine popcorn and nuts. Set aside. In small bowl, combine margarine, mustard and salad dressing mix. Pour over popcorn mixture, tossing to coat well. Spread in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes. Remove from oven; stir in raisins. Spread on paper towel to cool. Store in airtight container. Yields 6 cups.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Add soy sauce for flavor.
Feeds 4 people well.

title: cranberry sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill at least 3 hours. Yield:
2-1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin bread (caribbean)
directions: Beat together brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs,
one at a time, and
beat
well
after each addition.
Mix
in
vanilla extract. Sift all dry ingredients together and
beat into the batter gradually,
alternating with the
coconut
milk
until smooth. Stir in pumpkin puree with a wooden spoon and fold in nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans
and
set
on middle rack of 350° oven until bread tests done.
Cool in pans on
rack for about 30 minutes, then unmold on
rack
and
cool completely.
Good warm with butter.

title: belgium waffles
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of this mixture.
Mix eggs separately.
Put eggs, vanilla and melted margarine in the well.
Stir well.
Scoop approximately 1 teaspoon of batter in each square of waffle iron.
Using medium setting, cook until lightly browned.
If cookies tend to dry out, place a slice of bread inside container.

title: oven-fried vegetables(low-fat)
directions: Spray cold baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Set aside.
In a 9-inch pie plate, stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika until well mixed.
In a mixing bowl, place vegetables. Drizzle vegetables with salad dressing.
Toss until coated.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place vegetables in single layer on baking sheet. Bake in a 450° oven for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: maraschino splash
directions: Combine everything but the maraschino cherry in a shaker and shake until well combined.
Pour in a tall glass and add the cherry.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the potatoes, vanilla, milk and eggs.
Place in baking dish.
Stir the margarine, sugar and flour to make a topping.
Add the pecans (1 cup) on top and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: white clam sauce over linguine
directions: In saucepan, heat oil and garlic; saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and clam juice, wine, red pepper flakes and salt.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add minced clams, baby clams and parsley.
Return to boil and remove from heat.
Cook linguine according to package and then serve with sauce.

title: grandmother's brown beans
directions: Soak the beans in hot water for 10 minutes.
Bring to boil 4 cups of water.
Add the bacon or ham hock; add beans.
Boil for 3 hours.
Lower flame; cook until juice thickens.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in oblong dish.
Sprinkle celery over lettuce, then onions, peppers, eggs, peas and bacon bits.
Spread mayonnaise over all these ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: angel sweets
directions: Sift the sugar.
Melt chocolate and butter over low heat. Remove from heat; blend in egg.
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows, blending well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.
Makes about 48.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients. Serve with apple slices.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti.
Saute sausage.
Drain fat.
Saute onion and pepper.
Mix sausage, cheese, onion and pepper with ziti.
Pour on a jar of spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 3/4-inch balls and flatten with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Cool completely before removing.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and lemon juice.
Add onion juice and stir thoroughly.
Add salad oil slowly, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat for a few minutes.
Store in a cool place or refrigerator.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In a large bowl, lay your lettuce, celery, onion and peas. Spread mayonnaise.
Sprinkle peas with sugar and cheese.
Cover airtight.
Refrigerate several hours.
Before serving, toss. Garnish with tomato and croutons.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix everything together at once and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water; drain.
Melt margarine in pan. Add flour and blend.
Add milk gradually.
Stir in cheese.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Alternate cabbage and cheese sauce in dish.
Top with buttered bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread hash browns over 1 stick melted oleo in a baking dish. Mix soup, sour cream, onions, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spread over hash browns.
Mix corn flakes with 1/3 stick oleo and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cumin and cayenne spiced cashews
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Whisk egg white with 1 tablespoon water until foamy.
Add cashews and toss until coated.
Strain nuts; shake and drain for 2 minutes.
Wipe out bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Add nuts and toss until coated.
Spread nuts on
a large baking sheet in a single layer and bake for 40 minutes. Stir with a spatula and reduce temperature to 200°.
Bake 30 minutes longer until dry.
Use spatula to loosen from sheet.
Let dry completely and store in an airtight container up to 1 week.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and cherries in ungreased, square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Spread evenly.
Mix baking mix, nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake in 375° oven until brown, about 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Spoon pie filing over top of pie.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; stir in eggs and pumpkin and blend in dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake about 70 minutes at 350° or until done when tested in the middle with toothpick.

title: yum-yum pie
directions: Combine graham crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Add egg whites and sugar.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chewy macaroon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg yolks and salt together.
Add sugar 1/2 at a time.
Blend well.
Beat in milk, butter, lemon juice and almond extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites and coconut in egg yolk mixture.
Pour filling into frozen pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Mix okra, green tomatoes, Jiffy mix and flour.
Put in skillet with hot oil and turn down heat.
Stir frequently to keep from scorching.

title: piglickin' cake
directions: Mix together the above ingredients and bake according to box.

title: easy boston cream pie
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
When cool, cut into small squares.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour pudding over cake and garnish with nondairy topping.
If you like, add cherries.

title: granola
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Spread in large shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Stir often as it browns and burns easily.
Serve "as is" with milk or use in cookies and bread.

title: old fashioned rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar with rhubarb.
Mix eggs with sugar and rhubarb.
Mix all other dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Turn into 9-inch pastry shell and bake in oven, preheated to 450°, for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350°.
Continue baking until done.
Cool and add meringue and brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
