directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, margarine, syrup, vanilla, flour, salt and pecans. Bake at 350° until done.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together cream, milk, eggs, mustard and pepper. Meanwhile, cook bacon.
Break up bacon and put in bottom of pie shell.
Spread cheese on top of bacon.
Pour egg mixture over top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes to an hour. Put knife between center and edge to check if done.
It should be fairly clean.
During last 15 minutes, add strips of bacon to top of quiche, if desired.

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Cut cookies in half.
Fill and put together, making a mini cream puff.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Heat oil, saute
chopped
garlic.
Toss in seafoods and saute for 3 to
minutes.
Add	wine,
half
and half, lemon wedge, parsley and
cheese.
Heat linguine and arrange seafood on top. Serve with garlic toast.

title: sugarless cranberry sauce
directions: In medium-sized saucepan, combine rinsed cranberries, orange juice and water.
Stir over medium heat until berries pop.
Add chopped oranges and rind.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 cups.
Rich in vitamin C and delicious!

title: beef stroganoff (governor jim guy tucker's favorite recipe)(grandma's recipe)
directions: Trim fat from beef and cut filet crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cut each slice across grain into 1/2-inch wide strips (about 2 inches long).
Slowly heat large, heavy skillet.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter; add beef strips, just enough to cover skillet bottom.
Over high heat, sear quickly on all sides.
Remove with tongs as meat finishes browning (it should be brown on outside and rare on inside).

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly in medium bowl with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened.
Bake in greased muffin tins or use cupcake papers at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; stir in chopped dates, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until too heavy to move spoon.
Turn out on cloth sprinkled with 1/2 cup powdered sugar, mixed with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Roll firmly into a roll (like sausage).
Refrigerate until easy to slice.

title: potato soup
directions: Pour mixture over potatoes and stir.

title: chicken and leeks
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut leeks up to dark green, then cut light green part of stem into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Cut those pieces in half lengthwise and rinse.
Flake or pull apart leaves and put in frying pan along with oil and garlic.
Saute until soft. Add chicken, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Warm chicken.
Add cream and cook until cream is "saucy" 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add 2 eggs and the vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour; mix well, until mixture is stiff.
Add chocolate chips; mix well.
Place teaspoonfuls of mix onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine and chill.
Yield: Approximately 1 pint.

title: a. r. p. punch
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a gallon jar and mix.
Add water to fill jar.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add chilled ginger ale.
I add green food coloring.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients for meatballs except for Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Color meatballs with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake until crisp at 500° and drain grease.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in microwave bowl.
Blend in flour with whisk until smooth.
Gradually add milk and continue to blend well. Add other ingredients and microwave on High about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine flour and soda and sift into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts and mix.
Add mashed bananas.
Pour into 2 greased (or spray with Pam) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour half of the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove and set aside to cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Spread refried beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix salsa with hamburger; pour over refried beans.
Cover with Saran wrap and microwave 4 minutes.
Add cheese; cover and microwave 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Spread sour cream on top.
Add garnishes of your choice and serve with tortilla chips and lettuce.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and eggs.
Add milk and mashed bananas.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Combine with creamed mixture and mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, layer in casserole dish; asparagus, soup, bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly and crumbs are browned.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth and fluffy.
Break cake in small pieces and place in bottom of pan.
Spread with filling, then add more cake pieces.
Top with fruit filling and refrigerate overnight or until set.

title: tuna shortcake
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat, stirring often. Thicken, if necessary.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: gooey cheesecake
directions: Mix well.
Spread dough in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Mix butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Add Cheez Whiz, Velveeta, Cheddar and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until cheese is melted. Add sliced eggs and mushrooms.
Serve over toasted English muffins and sliced Canadian bacon.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and
onion	together.
Mash; add margarine, eggs and soup in dish.
Bake
at
for
10 to 15 minutes. Add cheese and crackers.
Return to oven to brown.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine sugar and eggs, then add oil and blend well. Add pumpkin; mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Add water. Beat well and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° until done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add pudding mix.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until thick.
Cool slightly; add gelatin.
Set aside.
Cover bottom of pie shell with strawberries.
Add gelatin mixture.
Top with whipped cream. Chill.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Whip all ingredients with mixer.
Place in medium bowl and refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.
This salad adds a spark to any meal.

title: cream mints
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sugar a little at a time, until mixture is stiff enough to knead.
Knead until smooth and creamy. Roll into small balls and roll in fine coconut.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate marble loaf cake
directions: Stir the shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Combine chocolate, water and soda; add to 1/2 the batter.
Alternate light and dark batters by spoonfuls in paper-lined 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Cool and frost with creamy chocolate frosting.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Cook the cabbage in a large pan.
Fry hamburger and onion together. Add tomatoes, red beans and other ingredients.
Simmer.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, powdered sugar, milk and whipped cream together. Spoon the mixture into the pie crust. Drizzle chocolate sauce over the top. Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch pecan coffee cake
directions: Grease 12 cup Bundt pan.
Spread pecans on bottom of pan. Place frozen rolls as evenly as possible in pan.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
In a saucepan on medium heat, melt and stir together butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour this mixture over rolls. Cover with towel and let stand in cool, draft-free place overnight. Do not refrigerate.
Next morning after rolls have risen, bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry rice
directions: Spray pan with butter flavored spray.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Cook until hot.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Pour in 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook, over medium heat, for 10 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water and rice.
Cover and continue to cook, over low heat, for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl; add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans; turn out on rack and cool completely.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in oil until limp.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Add milk, spices and clams just before serving and bring to a boil.
Allow to cook a few minutes before serving.

title: cheesy broccoli & rice
directions: Combine rice mix and water in saucepan, bring to a boil. Stir in 2/3 Cup french fried onions, vegetables and cheese. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 Cup onions over rice just before serving.

title: fruit salad mixup
directions: Use 3/4 cup pineapple and orange juice; boil and add to gelatin.
Add ice cubes; stir 5 minutes until thickened.
Remove ice.
Stir in sour cream.
Reserve 1/2 cup pineapple, 1/4 cup oranges and 1 tablespoon walnuts for garnish.
Stir remaining fruit and walnuts into gelatin with marshmallows.
Top with reserved fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna, broccoli and shells
directions: Steam broccoli, covered, in 2 inches of boiling water until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli with remaining ingredients.
Toss gently until combined.
Chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ever-ready coleslaw
directions: Place the first 7 ingredients in a
quart container and microwave 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture boils.
Cool and pour over the cabbage, pepper, onion and pimento all chopped together.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for pound cake for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes then remove from pans.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add zucchini, celery, potato and parsley.
Cook together until vegetables are softened. Add chicken broth (or 2 cups water and 2 chicken bouillon cubes), pepper and salt.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Put through blender; adjust seasonings.
May be served hot or cold.

title: corn relish
directions: Peel husks and silk from corn.
Trim blemishes.
Boil corn 5 minutes, then quickly dip in cold water.
Cut kernels from cob; measure 2 1/2 quarts cut corn.
Combine corn with onions and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pack into clean jars to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Immediately adjust covers (lids) as jar manufacturer directs.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda into a large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once.
Stir until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in cranberries.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, 2/3 cup full.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened; stir constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 tablespoons oleo.
Stir well.
Serve over ice cream, cake or pie. Refrigerate leftovers in sealed jar.

title: deviled crab
directions: Put 3 tablespoons butter in pan and lightly saute onions. (Before, rinse crab meat in cold water and remove ligaments if any.)
Stir flour in butter mixture; add milk gradually and cook mixture until it thickens.
Add slightly beaten egg yolk and crab meat, then season with Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, sage, pepper and red pepper.
Cook 3 minutes, then stir in parsley and lemon juice.
Fill crab shells with the mixture, then sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in an oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carousel mandarin chicken
directions: Combine chicken, celery, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Add mayonnaise, grapes, oranges and almonds to chicken mixture and toss well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place overlapping slices in a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and oil. Brush potato slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are done and browned at edges.
Serve immediately.

title: skillet vegetable pork chops
directions: Lightly sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Brown pork chops on both sides. Reduce heat.
Drain tomatoes and add liquid to pork chops. Coarsely chop tomatoes and add to pork chops; stir in rice.
Place a green pepper ring on each chop.
Cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chili(meatless)
directions: In large saucepan, cook the onion and green pepper in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add beans, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Stir in chili powder, salt, pepper and remaining water; bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, then layer other ingredients in the order given.
Do not mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Combine first six ingredients and shape into 18 balls and place in skillet.

title: super chippers
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together salt, baking powder, soda and flour.
Add along with vanilla to butter mixture.
Grind oatmeal until fine in food processor and add with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: marinated olives
directions: Discard brine from the jar of olives and slice olives the long way 4 times.
Return olives to jar and fill with water.
Change water frequently for 1 day and keep refrigerated at all times. Drain the water and put olives in a big pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix everything with olives and put back into jar. Refrigerate for at least 4 days, turning over frequently.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter or spray a large, long casserole dish.
Mix both stuffings and put half in dish.
Mix soups, sour cream and chicken. Spoon over stuffing.
Layer other half of stuffing over this.
Melt butter in chicken broth and carefully spoon on top.
Cook about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In large pot boil noodles according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, brown beef or turkey, onion and celery until meat is browned and celery is tender.
Drain fat.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the noodles and cheese.
Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour meat mixture and drained noodles into a 3-quart baking dish and mix.
Then top with cheese and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great with garlic bread and salad.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and mix well with Jell-O.
Add sour cream and fold in whipped topping.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and mix.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; mix well.
Add applesauce and mix.
Stir in nuts, oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: sweet pickled beans
directions: Cook large green or yellow string beans in salted water until tender.
Put
in sterile jars. Cover with equal parts of sugar and vinegar
that
have been brought to a boil.
Add one clove of garlic
that
has
been slit and a pinch of dried red pepper to each
jar.	Seal
in jars.	Ready to use in 10 days. Yield: 4 pints.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir until blended.

title: red cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add and beat until fluffy the eggs.
Sift together the flour and cocoa.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Dissolve the baking soda in the vinegar. Add to batter.
Mix in the food coloring.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mustardy fried chicken breasts
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
In a bowl, beat together egg and mustard. In separate bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs, mixing well.

title: mama's old timey pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add 6 egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add baking soda to sour cream and stir well.
Add flour and sour cream to creamed mixture alternately, beginning with flour and ending with flour, mixing well after each addition.
Beat 6 egg whites until fluffy and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana date nut cake
directions: In food processor or blender, process bananas until pureed. In large bowl, combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat in bananas, butter and sour cream. Stir in dates and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Dust with powdered sugar before serving.
Serves 12.

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Brown together the hamburger, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, onion dip and 1/2 beef when smooth.
Roll in remainder of beef that was chipped in blender.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet on stove over medium heat.
Add rice and cook, stirring 5 minutes.
Add meat, green onions, ginger, pepper and peas.
Push rice mix to side.
Break eggs into middle of skillet.
Cook, stirring 1 minute, and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and place meat, cut up in pieces, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the soup and chicken broth; pour over chicken.
In another bowl, combine margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix to form a batter.
Pour over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes until top is brown.

title: alice's roast
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Put onion soup mix on top of roast.
Pour mushroom soup and water around roast.
Cover with heavy foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes and cook for 2 more hours.

title: tater topped casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Saute chopped onion and celery.
Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain off fat and add salt to taste.
Spread meat, onion and celery in baking dish.
Pour undiluted celery soup over everything.
Add chopped pimentos for garnish.
Top with 16 ounce package of Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 5.

title: hot cheesy potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, green onions and celery. Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Spread half of Cheez Whiz over this and repeat layers.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until potatoes are tender.

title: carol's creole black beans
directions: *Andouille or Tasso is preferred but in a pinch Italian sausage will do.

title: mint chocolate chip drops
directions: Whip the egg whites stiff, adding the sugar. Beat.
Add the salt and chocolate mint chips.
Mix.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Put in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven about 12 hours.
If using plain chocolate chips, add mint flavoring.

title: for kids only play dough!
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook on high, stirring constantly.
Let cool and let the kids play.
It's edible too!

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Put one layer of beans, then sour cream, taco sauce (salsa) and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Let
stand for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle additional powdered sugar over the balls.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pistachio pudding mix over pineapple.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients and serve on lettuce leaf.
Freezes good.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix cream, sugar and beaten eggs together.
Melt butter or margarine; cool a little and beat into egg mixture.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 additional minutes or until pie filling is brown on top and shakes like jelly in the center.

title: orange chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix together brown sugar, cornstarch, ginger, orange marmalade, orange juice and lemon.
Add to chicken in frying pan.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 25 to 35 minutes, until tender.
Add 1 thinly sliced orange.
Simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball or log
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball or log.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine onion, chicken broth, cream, bay leaf, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Wash potatoes, cut into 1/4-inch slices and arrange in overlapping pattern in baking dish.
Gently pour broth mixture over potatoes.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove cover and baste potatoes with juices in pan. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes longer.

title: texas tumble weed
directions: Put white chocolate in a large bowl.
Place in microwave until melted, stirring frequently.
Pour shoe string potatoes into white chocolate and mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool and cut.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions, peppers and celery in one stick of butter or margarine, then add cheese, soup, two cups broth and lemon juice.
Cut up chicken and add to mixture.
Cook noodles as directed on package except use broth instead of water.
When done, mix everything together.
Place in casserole dish.
Heat and serve.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add milk with baking soda.
Add flour and salt.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done in a 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: salad nicoise
directions: Blanch green beans; marinate in small amount salad dressing for 2 hours.
Arrange lettuce on bottom and sides of large bowl. Mound potato salad in center.
Flake tuna fish on and around potato salad.
Layer green beans, tomato, eggs and black olives. Dress and toss at the table.

title: famous crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot sprayed with Pam.
Cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Double recipe to fill a large crock pot.

title: three herb popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large container or oven

roasting pan. salt to taste, set aside. Melt butter in a small saucepan. Remove from heat, stir in spices. Drizzle butter mixture over popcorn and toss lightly to coat evenly. Stir in nuts if desired.

title: sparkling orange punch
directions: In a large container, combine orange juice, lemonade and water.
Chill mixture.
Add lemon-lime drink just before serving. Makes 24 (1/2 cup) punch cup servings.

title: roquefort chicken
directions: Rub the broilers with salt and pepper.
Melt the butter in skillet.
Brown the chicken.
Remove from skillet and place in a baking dish.
Mash Roquefort cheese with a fork and blend in garlic and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water and boil until tender; debone and cut into small pieces.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup and hot broth until smooth; pour over chicken. Crush Ritz crackers into very small crumbs, mix poppy seed with crackers and spread over other ingredients.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal. Toss apple with water and lemon juice. Spoon into greased 8-inch casserole dish and sprinkle with flour mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: mad mod mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add onions and green pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in sauce mix, tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine meat sauce and noodles; mix lightly.
In a 2 quart casserole, layer half the noodle mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit loaf
directions: Mix.
Line loaf pan with brown paper, grease well.
Then put waxed paper on top of brown paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage and egg casserole(a hearty breakfast)
directions: Mix the soup and 1/4 cup milk together.
Mix in a blender: eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk, salt and dry mustard.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half the bread, sausage and cheese.
Repeat the layers. Pour soup over the layers and egg mixture.
Let set 12 hours in refrigerator or freeze ahead.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown and saute together green peppers, onion, celery and sausage.
Drain, if necessary.
Stir together soy sauce, water and rice; add to sausage mixture.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Put mushrooms on top.
Put frozen vegetables on top of mushrooms.
Cover and bake until liquid is absorbed, about 45 minutes.
Stir vegetables in, let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: beef barbecue
directions: In electric fry pan or large skillet brown beef with onion. Add salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture.
Heat to boiling then reduce and simmer.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs alternating with flour and sour cream. Add soda and vanilla. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in large tube pan.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and red pepper; cut in shortening and cheese until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Blend together the sugar, salt, flour and cornstarch; stir in water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir a little of this hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Combine mixes and cook a minute longer, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, rind and butter. Pour into baked shell.
Cool.
Top with meringue.

title: baked flounder italian style
directions: Shake fillets with bread crumbs in a bag until well coated. Arrange aluminum foil on a cookie sheet; lightly grease the foil. Place fillets on foil.

title: butterfly bites
directions: Cut celery in half crosswise.
Fill with cheese, add 2 pretzel wings.
Use pieces of pretzels for antennae and raisins for decoration.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil in saucepan over high heat. Stir mixture
until sugar is dissolved; lower heat to a simmer. Add
peppers;
simmer 10 minutes (while skimming foam from top). Stir in
pectin
and
bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from
heat.
Let
stand
for
20 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal with paraffin.

title: kyle's rice and shrimp gumbo
directions: In a large saucepan, combine onion and green pepper and saute in 1/4 cup of water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes. Add garlic, basil and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of water and rice; bring to a boil.
Add frozen shrimp.
Return to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until rice is tender and shrimp are pink.

title: pralines 2
directions: Put all of the ingredients except margarine and vanilla in a heavy boiler and cook at 232° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until candy begins to thicken and loses its glaze.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: sweet lemon chicken
directions: Flour and salt fryer and fry in cooking oil.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Simmer 45 to 50 minutes. Serve over steamed rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until thick.
Remove unmelted ice.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit.
Chill.
Spoon into crust.

title: apple fritters
directions: To make batter, beat egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and beat just until smooth.
Peel and core apples. Slice in 1/4-inch rings.
Dip in batter and drop into skillet containing 1/2-inch hot grease.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over fritters or roll in confectioners sugar.
Serve at once.
Yields 16 to 20 fritters.

title: b.l.t. pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse under cold water, drain, and transfer to large bowl.
Add bacon, tomatoes, and lettuce. 2. In small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt, and pepper.
Toss mayonnaise mixture with pasta and serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken almond
directions: Skin uncooked chicken breast; cut in thin strips.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons soy sauce; marinate for 10 minutes.
Beat flour, salt and eggs until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter; fry in hot oil (370°) until browned.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Add chicken broth to skillet.
Mix in bamboo shoots, chestnuts, celery and 2 tablespoons monosodium glutamate.
Bring to boil; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and cold water; add to chicken mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add chicken, almonds and salt to taste.
Cut lettuce in strips and toss with mixture just before serving over hot, fluffy rice.

title: cherry's salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand thoroughly and let stand covered in refrigerator overnight.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand several hours before serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour on hot griddle until done.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix
pineapple, juice and all, with pudding mix.
Drain fruit cocktail.
Add other ingredients.
Stir all together and chill.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cornflakes and ground beef
directions: Scramble lean ground beef.
Drain.
Pour dry cornflakes in a bowl.
Pour ground beef over the cornflakes.
Add ketchup to suit your taste.
Mix and enjoy.

title: cheesecake recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites on high until stiff while gradually pouring in the cup of sugar.

Cut each brick of cream cheese in half and beat into the egg whites until smooth. Pour in the teaspoon of vanilla and beat until thoroughly mixed. Spray cooking spray into a 9 inch spring form pan 3 inches deep. Dust the pan with the one cup of graham cracker crumbs.
Pour the mixture into the pan and bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until the cake doesn't look or shake like soup.
Take the cake out of the oven and heat the oven to 450°.
Mix in another bowl the sour cream, 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour mixture onto the cheesecake and put it back in the oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown on the edges.
Chill for at least two hours.
Overnight is best.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls or crescents with 1 tablespoon of dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: fried apple pies
directions: I take Hungry Jack biscuits or Texas biscuits or Big Country and sprinkle flour on your board and roll out to desired size. Add about 3 Tbsp. apple mixture to each one and fold over sealing ends all around pricking with fork.
Fry in oil or crisco.

title: nancy sherman special
directions: Saute sausage and flank steak with garlic for 3 to 5 minutes. Place in slow cooker with soup; cook on low 5 hours.
Dice pepper and onion; saute each with garlic salt (separately) and add to meat mixture.
Stir until peppers and onions thoroughly mixed and serve over rice or noodles.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Add the crushed vanilla wafers alternately with the milk.
Add the pecans and coconut.
Pour batter into a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gingered pineapple lamb
directions: Preheat broiler.
Meanwhile, trim fat from chops.
Place chops on the unheated rack of broiler pan.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Turn chops over and broil for 4 to 6 minutes until desired doneness.
Make sauce in a small saucepan.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in pineapple juice, green peppers, soy sauce and ginger.
Cook, stirring mixture until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Serve sauce over chops.

title: chocolate-cherry thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup melted chips; mix well.
Stir in oats, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Cover.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press centers with thumb.
Place cherry into each center. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Drizzle cookies with remaining melted chips.

title: beefy noodle stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven. Add beef and brown. Add broth. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer. Cover and simmer until meat is tender. Bring soup to a boil. Add noodles and cook until tender (around 10 minutes). Stir in cream of mushroom soup, drained mushrooms and sour cream.

title: louisiana chicken wings
directions: Wash wings; split at each joint and discard tips.
Deep fry at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes until crispy.
Drain well.
Melt butter and combine with hot sauce. Dip wings in sauce.
Serves 8 to 10 as an appetizer.

title: ham on pineapple
directions: Add mustard and mayonnaise to ground ham; mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Place patties on top of pineapple slices.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add the butter and vanilla.

title: kniphla
directions: Using water a little at a time, mix ingredients.
Work until stiff.
Drop teaspoon size into boiling water, lightly salted. Cook about 5 minutes.
Garnish with fried bread crullers.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and stuffing mix. Combine soup and sour cream. Spread over stuffing. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until meat juices run clear.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve both Jell-O's in 4 cups of boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water and juice from pineapple.
Add other ingredients.

title: coffee date loaf
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, instant coffee and sugar.
Add nuts and dates.

title: easy crepes
directions: Mix flour and eggs.
Add milk, a little at a time, mixing well each time.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Place in blender; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Shred chipped beef and combine with cream cheese which has been softened; add green pepper, onion and black pepper.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into small baking dish, top with pecans and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 10.

title: bread dressing
directions: Combine bread crumbs, onion, parsley, beaten egg, seasonings and enough stock or water to make a dressing which will hold together.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Makes 3 cups.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, onion, celery, water and milk in medium saucepan. Add salt, dill weed and butter.
Simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: vicki's ginger soy chicken
directions: Combine all
sauce
ingredients
and pour over chicken. Bring slowly to
a simmer.
Cook 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
(If sauce
thickens too much, add more water.) Leftover sauce keeps indefinitely
in glass jar, refrigerated.
Serves 6.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Mix together juice, tomatoes, salt, and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Tear canned biscuits in pieces and drop into juice mixture. Cook until done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, creaming well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour to creamed mixture, stirring until combined.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10 inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Grease and flour lined pan; tap out excess.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa powder, cornstarch, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, using an electric mixer set on medium speed, beat egg yolks and 1/4 c. sugar until fluffy.
In a small bowl, using clean beaters, beat egg whites on high until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 c. sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry, peaks form.
Fold 1/3 beaten egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Alternately fold in remaining whites and flour mixture.
Pour batter in pan; smooth top.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all above ingredients and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot deep oil until golden brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Marinate in salad dressing, celery and mayonnaise overnight.
Cover with Cheez Whiz and bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour until cheese becomes bubbly.
Spread with French fried onions and bake 5 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Spread cake mix over pie filling.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Delicious topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onions and butter.
Mix eggs and milk until blended.
Add corn and corn bread mix.
Spread batter into pan.
Spread onions over batter and sour cream over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 425° until puffed and golden.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: swiss steak
directions: Saute onion and pepper in hot fat.
Remove from skillet. Brown steaks slightly; salt and pepper to taste.
Place steaks in casserole pan in single layer, if possible.
Mash canned tomatoes; add sugar.
Mix in onion and pepper.
Spoon vegetables over steak.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° all day or all night.

title: broccoli-spinach casserole
directions: Cook the spinach and broccoli, a little less than instructions say, adding a tablespoon of vinegar to each.
Add the seasonings to the soup and then mix in drained spinach and broccoli.
Pour into a flat, buttered baking dish and arrange onions on top.
(If you want, also add 2 peeled and quartered tomatoes.)
Sprinkle on the cheese and bake for 35 minutes at 325° or for 45 minutes at 250°.
(If you double this recipe, use a can each of mushroom and celery soups.)

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks together and mix thoroughly.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and water. Add butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue from the egg whites.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Using a large Tupperware bowl, sift cocoa and sugar together. Place butter on top and add milk.
Microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir and add nuts.
Spread in a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
